	(2140,3,'2017-07-13 12:43:13','2017-07-13 17:43:13','[section container=\"true\" row=\"true\" full_col=\"true\"]\r\n<div class=\"text-center p15 mb20\" role=\"alert\" style=\"background: RGBA(252, 248, 227, 1.00)\">\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 20px;\">If you add a Shortcode(s) please <b>document it</b>. I created a <a href=\"http://sushiexperience.com.test/shortcodes/documentation-template/\"><b>template for documentation (click me)</b></a> that should make it easy to write some docs. This theme has had <b>multiple</b> updates since 3/10/2017 but the Patch Notes show the theme hasn\'t been updated in months. Anytime a change is made that impacts the theme or gives it added/changed functionality, it needs to be communicated in the Patch Notes and the themes Version needs to be changed (found in functions.php).</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h1>Version [version]</h1>\r\n<h2>PATCH NOTES</h2>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.12.0 - 4/1/2017 - 7/13/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Updated Bower Components</li>\r\n<li>Brought in latest Font Awesome package.</li>\r\n<li>Created a basic <a href=\"http://sushiexperience.com.test/shortcodes/documentation-template/\">template for documentation</a>. Anytime a new shortcode is added, copy and paste the markup in that page as your starting point.</li>\r\n<li>New \"Example Local Service\" page template added</li>\r\n<li>New \"Example Professional Service\" page template added</li>\r\n<li>New \"Example Product Page\" template added</li>\r\n<li>Social Blocks shortcode added to display stylized social media blocks that tell users to \"Follow\".</li>\r\n<li>Social Sharing Squares shortcode added which share the content on a blog post through the user\'s social media account.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.11.1 -  3/10/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>back-up in project folder</li>\r\n<li>Brand New Mobile Menu</li>\r\n<li>The Desktop Menu and Mobile Menu no longer share the same links. You\'ll need to modify the mobile menu in the wordpress backend when you set up the primary menu.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.9 - 3/7/2017 - 3/8/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><code>single-event.php</code> has been rebuilt to better accommodate content and pictures.</li>\r\n<li>New example page \'Home\'</li>\r\n<li>The `gutter` and `gutter_bottom` options from Block Grid have now been added to the gallery shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>All Styles are being enqued the \"right\" way. The bottom of functions.php has this code if your interested on how this is done.</li>\r\n<li>All JavaScript is being enqued the \"right\" way. The bottom of functions.php has this code if your interested on how this is done.</li>\r\n<li>Added CSS prefixes throughout less files.</li>\r\n<li>Same height for event system loop.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.8 - 3/7/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Plugin updates.</li>\r\n<li>Font Weight Classes Added. <code>.fw-{desired-font-weight}</code></li>\r\n<li>The max-width classes bug is gone.</li>\r\n<li>Removed trash ass parallax plugin. </li>\r\n<li>New option <code>full_col</code> for the section shortcode. See the docs for the details.</li>\r\n<li>The <code>placehold</code> shortcode is now for LOREM IPSUM TEXT ONLY. The only new REQUIRED option is <code>lines=\"\"</code> where you feed the number of sentences.</li>\r\n<li>New option for the <code>bc_img</code> shortcode <code>dummy</code>. Since we use a lot of placeholder images, this option gives you the opportunity to feed ONLY THE DIMENSIONS to it and it will output a dummy image based on the dimensions given.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.7 - 3/3/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New file in <code>lib</code> for custom taxonomies. There is a basic function in that file that is commented out that will create a custom taxonomy, but a few of the $args need to change depending on the post type your trying to target with the custom tax.</li>\r\n<li>A lot of the CSS for the navbar has been cleaned up a lot. There was a specificity issue with the styles and sub menu was getting styles from top level links and all sorts of whack other stuff. This is all fixed now.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.6 - 2/24/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>There is a new textblock that will output a form for mailchimp. If you go into <code>mailchimpAjaxHandler.php</code> and pass your API Key and List ID to the proper variables, the form will do the rest for you. Again, this textblock WILL NOT work if you haven\'t set up those variables.</li>\r\n<li>A lot of the animation classes got an upgrade. Smoother, more linear look and they activate earlier instead of having to scroll all the way into the viewport to start the animation</li>\r\n<li>New function in functions.php called <code>build_event_schema($id)</code>. This function is only useable in a PhP file. You need to feed the <code>$post->ID</code> to the function and it will output proper Schema for the event in which you feed the id Event. Schema can be tested <a href=\"https://search.google.com/structured-data/testing-tool\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></li>\r\n<li>There is now a function for signing up subscribers to mailchimp that is easily used with an ajax call to the file.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.5 - 2/21/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[past_event_loop]]</code>. This will output the events that have passed. You need to have the Event module set up in order for this shortcode to execute.</li>\r\n<li>Clean up of some code</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.4 - 2/6/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li> New shortcode <code>[[bc_box]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li> New shortcode <code>[[image_slider]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li>General bug fixes and improvements.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.3 - 1/31/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Parallax is back! You can use this on the section, page banner and page banner large. just set parallax=\"true\" and make sure you give it a background=\"\".</li>\r\n<li>New mobile navbar layout</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.2 - 12/13/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reduced the padding on the contact form on mobile</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[bc_counter]]</code></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.1 - 12/12/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reduced the padding on the contact form on mobile</li>\r\n<li>New helpful script, Pressing <code>SHIFT + Z</code> (on the front end) will toggle the wpadminbar to show and not show.</li>\r\n<li>Board of Directors added.</li>\r\n<li>Style changes to the <a href=\"/blog/\">blog</a> loop</li>\r\n<li>Contact form error styles are better</li>\r\n<li>Set admin columns for Staff and Event posts</li>\r\n<li>single-staff.php added.</li>\r\n<li>LESS code cleanup</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[section_overlay_blend]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[share_links]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li>Changed some default fonts so these docs are nicer looking.</li>\r\n<li>New class - class=\"lh1\". Gives an element line-height: 1;</li>\r\n<li>More Demo Pages Added, see <a href=\"/modules/\">modules</a>.</li>\r\n<li>Few new animation classes created. <code>bc-fade-in-left</code> and <code>bc-fade-in-right</code>. Throw these on any element and it will fade in when scrolled to.</li>\r\n<li>New documentation page for Modules. This page explains how to use the newly implemented systems that take some configuration before starting to use them.</li>\r\n<li>New javascript file added called theme.js. This file was added to house all the javascript that is necessary for the theme to work properly. The main.js file was getting really crowded and it should now be used for website specific scripts.</li>\r\n<li>Bye Steph, your not a user anymore. Pwned.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode social_inline. See the docs for the details.</li>\r\n<li>New class text-fade added to the theme. Give to a piece of text, header, etc. and it will fade in when scrolled to.</li>\r\n<li>the img_overlay shortcode has been modified to look and work cleaner.</li>\r\n<li>The img shortcode has been modified. See the docs for all the new options.</li>\r\n<li>Change made to the header. We kept the Columns but just pulled the padding from them, so everything should work more fluidly.</li>\r\n<li>Admin Columns Pro with the ACF add-on has been added to the plugins.</li>\r\n<li>The staff system that was first implemented on UAP has been added to the theme. To get everything going, you need to uncomment the custom post type staff and use the <code>bc_staff_grid</code> shortcode. All the styles and javascript are ready to go. Styles can be found in textblocks-and-shortcodes.</li>\r\n<li>Food Menu system added to the theme. To get it going, make a page and set the template to Featured Menu and your good to go. Styles can be found in textblocks-shortcodes less file.</li>\r\n<li>Hours option added to Schema, Address Loop and Mobile Location Conversion shortcodes.</li>\r\n<li>Caption option added to the gallery shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>Custom Role code updated to have further control over custom roles.</li>\r\n<li>Event System added. To set up, active custom posts types in functions and the event post is already built into the custom post file. You also need to set the event custom fields to match post type event. Styles for the event card and single event are found in textblocks-shortcodes.less</li>\r\n<li>ALL bower components (such as bootstrap, slick, jquery, matchHeight, FontAwesome, etc) have all been updated to their most recent version available as of 11/16/2016.</li>\r\n<li>Libraries and Frameworks in Global Content has been deprecated, we\'re just going to bring in all the Bower Components.</li>\r\n<li>Business Hours added to the Global Content page, with the address and such.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed a bug with Gallery shortcode where the image wasn\'t responsive.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.17 - 11/8/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A 768x768 placeholder image has been added to the media uploads. We always seem to need placeholder post images and placeholder staff images, etc, so this will be nice to have in the media folder.</li>\r\n<li>There are no longer different footer layouts. The layout just lives in footer.php now</li>\r\n<li><code>mobile-text-center</code> class has been added to center on viewports under 768px.</li>\r\n<li>Change to the mobile nav dropdown links. There was an issue that if there were too many links, you weren\'t able to scroll down the mobile nav links, it would scroll the page behind it. That has now been fixed.</li>\r\n<li>search function now available for mobile. The variable to toggle it is in header.php</li>\r\n<li>the shortcode <code>single_location_address</code> has been deprecated. Just use <code>schema</code> instead.</li>\r\n<li>new option for the address_attr shortcode - <code>link</code>. See the <a href=\"/shortcodes/address-attribute/\">docs</a> for how to use it. </li>\r\n<li>container-fluid option now available for the section shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed a bug with Gallery shortcode where the image wasn\'t responsive.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.16 - 11/2/2016 - 11/3/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Breadcrumbs now have schema</li>\r\n<li>Search function now a part of the theme.</li>\r\n<li>Visual editor has been disabled for ALL USERS. (code for this is found in /lib/setup.php)</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The buttons for the mobile footer have been re-vamped to fit better.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.15 - 10/26/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Drop down menu for mobile is now a lot easier to touch on a mobile device, as well as having a new look.</a>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Changed some default accordion styles.</li>\r\n<li>Removed the formula we previously had for calculating height of logo for the navbar and spacing etc. It just wasn\'t consistent enough and all depended on what the companies logo looks like.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.14 - 10/21/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New classes added to change text color to the LESS variables color-1 and color-2</li>\r\n<li>Removed Stellar JS (the parallax plugin). It was way too buggy. We will need to investigate a new parallax option. This means that you can no longer use the \'parallax\' option for some of our shortcodes. Avoid using that option until further notice.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed bug with Block Grid that was causing it to always go 2 across on mobile.</li>\r\n<li>Removed some Text Blocks we never use.</li>\r\n<li>Section Split has been fixed to work better on all viewports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.13 - 09/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Minor fix to the video bg plugin.</li>\r\n<li>Big improvement to the <a href=\"/blog/\">blog</a> template.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The mobile logo and desktop logo for the navbar are now variables. Just plug in the path/to/file and it\'ll get injected for you.</li>\r\n<li>Changes visually to the sidebar with form textblock.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.12 - 09/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>So yea... section_video is gone. But fear not! We just made it easier to execute a video background. It is now built into the regular <code>section</code> shortcode. Peep the docs.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.11 - 09/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><code>underlay</code> option had been added to the <code>section</code> shortcode. Peep the docs for the 411.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.10 - 09/21/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><code>target</code> option added to bc_btn shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>New legitness section_video. Find out more about this badass shortcode [anchor href=\"http://sushiexperience.com.test/shortcodes/section-video/\" content=\"here\"].</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.9 - 09/15/2016 - 09/16/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Theme now supports sub-sub menu.</li>\r\n<li>Block grid has a new options <code>gutter</code>, <code>gutter_lower</code>, and <code>animate</code> . See the docs for more information.</li>\r\n<li>Icon Schema has been deprecated.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode Schema.</li>\r\n<li>Theme now supports companies with Fax numbers.</li>\r\n<li>BXSlider has been deprecated to make the switch to Slick Carousel. <a href=\"https://kenwheeler.github.io/slick/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link-color-2\">Slick Docs</a></li>\r\n<li>New shortcodes for slider. See the docs for more info.</a></li>\r\n<li>Slider, match height, and waypoints are no longer optional plugins. The theme relies on these too often so they are by default included in the theme.</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.8 - 09/12/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New class has been added <code>.section-split</code>. Using this class relies on your columns following a certain layout. See the docs for more info!</li>\r\n<li>A brand new page template has been added to the theme. This makes building over conversion pages (content left, sidebar right) a lot faster and it is basically automated now. When you create a new page, change the template to Sub Page Template and the rest is done for you. [anchor href=\"/page-template-sub-page/\" content=\"Here\"] is what the page looks like. If at any point you want to make edits to the template, just edit the <code>template-sub-page.php</code> file.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.7 - 09/09/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Stellar.JS has been added to the theme. This is not an optional plugin, it needs to always stay in the theme. Stellar allows parallax backgrounds. There is a new option on the section shortcode and the page_banner_large shortcode. Simply just set parallax=\"true\" and boom, you\'ll have parallax. Docs have been updated with new options.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.6 - 08/30/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New shortcode img_overlay</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode team_block</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode g_map</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.5 - 08/25/2016 - 08/29/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The excerpt read character length is now set to 20 characters. To change this, you can go into setup.php.</li>\r\n<li>The excerpt read more has been changed from WP\'s default [...] to just simply ... </li>\r\n<li>New tracking options for button and anchor.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode img_flex.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode page_banner_flex. </li>\r\n<li>Formulated mobile navbar calculations. </li>\r\n<li>The issue with nesting a col shortcode inside another col shortcode has been address. In WordPress you cannot nest shortcodes that use the same name, so nesting our column shortcode needed a work-around. If you want to nest a col inside another col you need to use <code>col_nested</code> for the nested columns. It works and has the same options as the col shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>The contact page form now has color validation. Red inset shadow gets added if req field is skipped over and green inset shadow is added if it has a value.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>ul\'s and ol\'s now have default 25px padding left and 10px margin bottom. Use <code>class=\"list-unstyled\"</code> if you don\'t want any styles to your list.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.4 - 08/23/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>New contact page form layout. There are by default two different forms. One that has labels and one that does not and uses placeholders instead.</li>\r\n<li>You can now toggle the admin bar on and off. This is especially useful when in development. Just uncomment the show_admin_bar(false) function to hide the admin bar.</li>\r\n<li>New LESS Mixin <code>placeholder-color(@color);</code>. See documentation for details.</li>\r\n<li>New classes <code>link-blend</code> <code>text-right</code> <code>text-left</code>. See documentation for more details.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>Big fixes to navbar active page. All the active styles now apply correctly.</li>\r\n<li>Fix to last of type link in navbar. There was a bug were it was giving styles we didn\'t want to the sub menu.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.3 - 08/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>Footer, Mobile Nav, Topbar and more use address attributes from Global Content to populate contact data.</li>\r\n<li>Bug fix to the placehold shortcode where it would return one extra sentence then what you asked for.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.2 - 08/19/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>New grid layout on navbar & logo display block.</li>\r\n<li>No padding-right on last-of-type navbar link. (css in !important on this rule)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.1 - 08/18/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>If an anchor tag has <code>#</code> as the href attribute, it will no longer make the page jump or add \"#\" to the end of the URL. It will simply do nothing at all.</li>\r\n<li>Login page now has the BrandCoders logo and clicking that logo now takes you to brandcoders.com. If you want to change these settings, you can find them in <code>lib/setup.php</code>.</li>\r\n<li>A default \'Thank You\' page has been implemented into theme and is already linked up to default contact form.</li>\r\n<li>The default buttons paddings have been increased on all sizes. They have <a href=\"https://foundation.zurb.com/sites/docs/v/5.5.3/components/buttons.html#button-sizing\" target=\"_blank\">foundations</a> sizes. They are a pretty good standard.</li>\r\n<li>New max width classes have been implemented into the theme. See classes and mixins for the documentation.</li>\r\n<li>New class <code>iframe-container</code>. Give to an element that is the parent of an iframe. It will make the iframe responsive.</li>\r\n<li><code>.bg-color-1</code> and <code>.bg-color-2</code> are now standard classes. See classes and mixins for the documentation.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>Changes to comments in code and code organization.</li>\r\n<li>Navbar z-index changed to 2001</li>\r\n<li>Buttons don\'t have buggy styles on active and focus anymore.</li>\r\n<li>Contact Form 7 Submit Buttons now Automatically use <code>color-1</code>.</li>\r\n<li>A featured image for the overall theme has been added. This is the picture that is shown when your go to appearance->themes in the WordPress backend.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/section]','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','4-revision-v1','','','2017-07-13 12:43:13','2017-07-13 17:43:13','',4,'http://sushiexperience.com.test/4-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(2141,3,'2017-07-13 13:00:54','2017-07-13 18:00:54','[section container=\"true\" row=\"true\" full_col=\"true\"]\r\n<div class=\"text-center p15 mb20\" role=\"alert\" style=\"background: RGBA(252, 248, 227, 1.00)\">\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 20px;\">If you add a Shortcode(s) please <b>document it</b>. I created a <a href=\"http://sushiexperience.com.test/shortcodes/documentation-template/\"><b>template for documentation (click me)</b></a> that should make it easy to write some docs. This theme has had <b>multiple</b> updates since 3/10/2017 but the Patch Notes show the theme hasn\'t been updated in months. Anytime a change is made that impacts the theme or gives it added/changed functionality, it needs to be communicated in the Patch Notes and the themes Version needs to be changed (found in functions.php).</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h1>Version [version]</h1>\r\n<h2>PATCH NOTES</h2>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.12.0 - 4/1/2017 - 7/13/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Updated Bower Components</li>\r\n<li>Brought in latest Font Awesome package.</li>\r\n<li>Created a basic <a href=\"http://sushiexperience.com.test/shortcodes/documentation-template/\">template for documentation</a>. Anytime a new shortcode is added, copy and paste the markup in that page as your starting point.</li>\r\n<li>New \"Example Local Service\" page template added</li>\r\n<li>New \"Example Professional Service\" page template added</li>\r\n<li>New \"Example Product Page\" template added</li>\r\n<li>Social Blocks shortcode added to display stylized social media blocks that tell users to \"Follow\".</li>\r\n<li>Social Sharing Squares shortcode added which share the content on a blog post through the user\'s social media account.</li>\r\n<li>Mobile Top CTA shortcode added along with capability to change buttons in the WYSIWIG editor.</li>\r\n<li>Middle CTA shortcode added that can be fully customized.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.11.1 -  3/10/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>back-up in project folder</li>\r\n<li>Brand New Mobile Menu</li>\r\n<li>The Desktop Menu and Mobile Menu no longer share the same links. You\'ll need to modify the mobile menu in the wordpress backend when you set up the primary menu.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.9 - 3/7/2017 - 3/8/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><code>single-event.php</code> has been rebuilt to better accommodate content and pictures.</li>\r\n<li>New example page \'Home\'</li>\r\n<li>The `gutter` and `gutter_bottom` options from Block Grid have now been added to the gallery shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>All Styles are being enqued the \"right\" way. The bottom of functions.php has this code if your interested on how this is done.</li>\r\n<li>All JavaScript is being enqued the \"right\" way. The bottom of functions.php has this code if your interested on how this is done.</li>\r\n<li>Added CSS prefixes throughout less files.</li>\r\n<li>Same height for event system loop.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.8 - 3/7/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Plugin updates.</li>\r\n<li>Font Weight Classes Added. <code>.fw-{desired-font-weight}</code></li>\r\n<li>The max-width classes bug is gone.</li>\r\n<li>Removed trash ass parallax plugin. </li>\r\n<li>New option <code>full_col</code> for the section shortcode. See the docs for the details.</li>\r\n<li>The <code>placehold</code> shortcode is now for LOREM IPSUM TEXT ONLY. The only new REQUIRED option is <code>lines=\"\"</code> where you feed the number of sentences.</li>\r\n<li>New option for the <code>bc_img</code> shortcode <code>dummy</code>. Since we use a lot of placeholder images, this option gives you the opportunity to feed ONLY THE DIMENSIONS to it and it will output a dummy image based on the dimensions given.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.7 - 3/3/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New file in <code>lib</code> for custom taxonomies. There is a basic function in that file that is commented out that will create a custom taxonomy, but a few of the $args need to change depending on the post type your trying to target with the custom tax.</li>\r\n<li>A lot of the CSS for the navbar has been cleaned up a lot. There was a specificity issue with the styles and sub menu was getting styles from top level links and all sorts of whack other stuff. This is all fixed now.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.6 - 2/24/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>There is a new textblock that will output a form for mailchimp. If you go into <code>mailchimpAjaxHandler.php</code> and pass your API Key and List ID to the proper variables, the form will do the rest for you. Again, this textblock WILL NOT work if you haven\'t set up those variables.</li>\r\n<li>A lot of the animation classes got an upgrade. Smoother, more linear look and they activate earlier instead of having to scroll all the way into the viewport to start the animation</li>\r\n<li>New function in functions.php called <code>build_event_schema($id)</code>. This function is only useable in a PhP file. You need to feed the <code>$post->ID</code> to the function and it will output proper Schema for the event in which you feed the id Event. Schema can be tested <a href=\"https://search.google.com/structured-data/testing-tool\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></li>\r\n<li>There is now a function for signing up subscribers to mailchimp that is easily used with an ajax call to the file.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.5 - 2/21/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[past_event_loop]]</code>. This will output the events that have passed. You need to have the Event module set up in order for this shortcode to execute.</li>\r\n<li>Clean up of some code</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.4 - 2/6/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li> New shortcode <code>[[bc_box]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li> New shortcode <code>[[image_slider]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li>General bug fixes and improvements.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.3 - 1/31/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Parallax is back! You can use this on the section, page banner and page banner large. just set parallax=\"true\" and make sure you give it a background=\"\".</li>\r\n<li>New mobile navbar layout</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.2 - 12/13/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reduced the padding on the contact form on mobile</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[bc_counter]]</code></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.1 - 12/12/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reduced the padding on the contact form on mobile</li>\r\n<li>New helpful script, Pressing <code>SHIFT + Z</code> (on the front end) will toggle the wpadminbar to show and not show.</li>\r\n<li>Board of Directors added.</li>\r\n<li>Style changes to the <a href=\"/blog/\">blog</a> loop</li>\r\n<li>Contact form error styles are better</li>\r\n<li>Set admin columns for Staff and Event posts</li>\r\n<li>single-staff.php added.</li>\r\n<li>LESS code cleanup</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[section_overlay_blend]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[share_links]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li>Changed some default fonts so these docs are nicer looking.</li>\r\n<li>New class - class=\"lh1\". Gives an element line-height: 1;</li>\r\n<li>More Demo Pages Added, see <a href=\"/modules/\">modules</a>.</li>\r\n<li>Few new animation classes created. <code>bc-fade-in-left</code> and <code>bc-fade-in-right</code>. Throw these on any element and it will fade in when scrolled to.</li>\r\n<li>New documentation page for Modules. This page explains how to use the newly implemented systems that take some configuration before starting to use them.</li>\r\n<li>New javascript file added called theme.js. This file was added to house all the javascript that is necessary for the theme to work properly. The main.js file was getting really crowded and it should now be used for website specific scripts.</li>\r\n<li>Bye Steph, your not a user anymore. Pwned.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode social_inline. See the docs for the details.</li>\r\n<li>New class text-fade added to the theme. Give to a piece of text, header, etc. and it will fade in when scrolled to.</li>\r\n<li>the img_overlay shortcode has been modified to look and work cleaner.</li>\r\n<li>The img shortcode has been modified. See the docs for all the new options.</li>\r\n<li>Change made to the header. We kept the Columns but just pulled the padding from them, so everything should work more fluidly.</li>\r\n<li>Admin Columns Pro with the ACF add-on has been added to the plugins.</li>\r\n<li>The staff system that was first implemented on UAP has been added to the theme. To get everything going, you need to uncomment the custom post type staff and use the <code>bc_staff_grid</code> shortcode. All the styles and javascript are ready to go. Styles can be found in textblocks-and-shortcodes.</li>\r\n<li>Food Menu system added to the theme. To get it going, make a page and set the template to Featured Menu and your good to go. Styles can be found in textblocks-shortcodes less file.</li>\r\n<li>Hours option added to Schema, Address Loop and Mobile Location Conversion shortcodes.</li>\r\n<li>Caption option added to the gallery shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>Custom Role code updated to have further control over custom roles.</li>\r\n<li>Event System added. To set up, active custom posts types in functions and the event post is already built into the custom post file. You also need to set the event custom fields to match post type event. Styles for the event card and single event are found in textblocks-shortcodes.less</li>\r\n<li>ALL bower components (such as bootstrap, slick, jquery, matchHeight, FontAwesome, etc) have all been updated to their most recent version available as of 11/16/2016.</li>\r\n<li>Libraries and Frameworks in Global Content has been deprecated, we\'re just going to bring in all the Bower Components.</li>\r\n<li>Business Hours added to the Global Content page, with the address and such.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed a bug with Gallery shortcode where the image wasn\'t responsive.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.17 - 11/8/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A 768x768 placeholder image has been added to the media uploads. We always seem to need placeholder post images and placeholder staff images, etc, so this will be nice to have in the media folder.</li>\r\n<li>There are no longer different footer layouts. The layout just lives in footer.php now</li>\r\n<li><code>mobile-text-center</code> class has been added to center on viewports under 768px.</li>\r\n<li>Change to the mobile nav dropdown links. There was an issue that if there were too many links, you weren\'t able to scroll down the mobile nav links, it would scroll the page behind it. That has now been fixed.</li>\r\n<li>search function now available for mobile. The variable to toggle it is in header.php</li>\r\n<li>the shortcode <code>single_location_address</code> has been deprecated. Just use <code>schema</code> instead.</li>\r\n<li>new option for the address_attr shortcode - <code>link</code>. See the <a href=\"/shortcodes/address-attribute/\">docs</a> for how to use it. </li>\r\n<li>container-fluid option now available for the section shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed a bug with Gallery shortcode where the image wasn\'t responsive.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.16 - 11/2/2016 - 11/3/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Breadcrumbs now have schema</li>\r\n<li>Search function now a part of the theme.</li>\r\n<li>Visual editor has been disabled for ALL USERS. (code for this is found in /lib/setup.php)</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The buttons for the mobile footer have been re-vamped to fit better.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.15 - 10/26/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Drop down menu for mobile is now a lot easier to touch on a mobile device, as well as having a new look.</a>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Changed some default accordion styles.</li>\r\n<li>Removed the formula we previously had for calculating height of logo for the navbar and spacing etc. It just wasn\'t consistent enough and all depended on what the companies logo looks like.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.14 - 10/21/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New classes added to change text color to the LESS variables color-1 and color-2</li>\r\n<li>Removed Stellar JS (the parallax plugin). It was way too buggy. We will need to investigate a new parallax option. This means that you can no longer use the \'parallax\' option for some of our shortcodes. Avoid using that option until further notice.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed bug with Block Grid that was causing it to always go 2 across on mobile.</li>\r\n<li>Removed some Text Blocks we never use.</li>\r\n<li>Section Split has been fixed to work better on all viewports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.13 - 09/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Minor fix to the video bg plugin.</li>\r\n<li>Big improvement to the <a href=\"/blog/\">blog</a> template.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The mobile logo and desktop logo for the navbar are now variables. Just plug in the path/to/file and it\'ll get injected for you.</li>\r\n<li>Changes visually to the sidebar with form textblock.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.12 - 09/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>So yea... section_video is gone. But fear not! We just made it easier to execute a video background. It is now built into the regular <code>section</code> shortcode. Peep the docs.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.11 - 09/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><code>underlay</code> option had been added to the <code>section</code> shortcode. Peep the docs for the 411.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.10 - 09/21/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><code>target</code> option added to bc_btn shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>New legitness section_video. Find out more about this badass shortcode [anchor href=\"http://sushiexperience.com.test/shortcodes/section-video/\" content=\"here\"].</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.9 - 09/15/2016 - 09/16/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Theme now supports sub-sub menu.</li>\r\n<li>Block grid has a new options <code>gutter</code>, <code>gutter_lower</code>, and <code>animate</code> . See the docs for more information.</li>\r\n<li>Icon Schema has been deprecated.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode Schema.</li>\r\n<li>Theme now supports companies with Fax numbers.</li>\r\n<li>BXSlider has been deprecated to make the switch to Slick Carousel. <a href=\"https://kenwheeler.github.io/slick/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link-color-2\">Slick Docs</a></li>\r\n<li>New shortcodes for slider. See the docs for more info.</a></li>\r\n<li>Slider, match height, and waypoints are no longer optional plugins. The theme relies on these too often so they are by default included in the theme.</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.8 - 09/12/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New class has been added <code>.section-split</code>. Using this class relies on your columns following a certain layout. See the docs for more info!</li>\r\n<li>A brand new page template has been added to the theme. This makes building over conversion pages (content left, sidebar right) a lot faster and it is basically automated now. When you create a new page, change the template to Sub Page Template and the rest is done for you. [anchor href=\"/page-template-sub-page/\" content=\"Here\"] is what the page looks like. If at any point you want to make edits to the template, just edit the <code>template-sub-page.php</code> file.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.7 - 09/09/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Stellar.JS has been added to the theme. This is not an optional plugin, it needs to always stay in the theme. Stellar allows parallax backgrounds. There is a new option on the section shortcode and the page_banner_large shortcode. Simply just set parallax=\"true\" and boom, you\'ll have parallax. Docs have been updated with new options.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.6 - 08/30/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New shortcode img_overlay</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode team_block</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode g_map</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.5 - 08/25/2016 - 08/29/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The excerpt read character length is now set to 20 characters. To change this, you can go into setup.php.</li>\r\n<li>The excerpt read more has been changed from WP\'s default [...] to just simply ... </li>\r\n<li>New tracking options for button and anchor.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode img_flex.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode page_banner_flex. </li>\r\n<li>Formulated mobile navbar calculations. </li>\r\n<li>The issue with nesting a col shortcode inside another col shortcode has been address. In WordPress you cannot nest shortcodes that use the same name, so nesting our column shortcode needed a work-around. If you want to nest a col inside another col you need to use <code>col_nested</code> for the nested columns. It works and has the same options as the col shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>The contact page form now has color validation. Red inset shadow gets added if req field is skipped over and green inset shadow is added if it has a value.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>ul\'s and ol\'s now have default 25px padding left and 10px margin bottom. Use <code>class=\"list-unstyled\"</code> if you don\'t want any styles to your list.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.4 - 08/23/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>New contact page form layout. There are by default two different forms. One that has labels and one that does not and uses placeholders instead.</li>\r\n<li>You can now toggle the admin bar on and off. This is especially useful when in development. Just uncomment the show_admin_bar(false) function to hide the admin bar.</li>\r\n<li>New LESS Mixin <code>placeholder-color(@color);</code>. See documentation for details.</li>\r\n<li>New classes <code>link-blend</code> <code>text-right</code> <code>text-left</code>. See documentation for more details.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>Big fixes to navbar active page. All the active styles now apply correctly.</li>\r\n<li>Fix to last of type link in navbar. There was a bug were it was giving styles we didn\'t want to the sub menu.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.3 - 08/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>Footer, Mobile Nav, Topbar and more use address attributes from Global Content to populate contact data.</li>\r\n<li>Bug fix to the placehold shortcode where it would return one extra sentence then what you asked for.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.2 - 08/19/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>New grid layout on navbar & logo display block.</li>\r\n<li>No padding-right on last-of-type navbar link. (css in !important on this rule)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.1 - 08/18/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>If an anchor tag has <code>#</code> as the href attribute, it will no longer make the page jump or add \"#\" to the end of the URL. It will simply do nothing at all.</li>\r\n<li>Login page now has the BrandCoders logo and clicking that logo now takes you to brandcoders.com. If you want to change these settings, you can find them in <code>lib/setup.php</code>.</li>\r\n<li>A default \'Thank You\' page has been implemented into theme and is already linked up to default contact form.</li>\r\n<li>The default buttons paddings have been increased on all sizes. They have <a href=\"https://foundation.zurb.com/sites/docs/v/5.5.3/components/buttons.html#button-sizing\" target=\"_blank\">foundations</a> sizes. They are a pretty good standard.</li>\r\n<li>New max width classes have been implemented into the theme. See classes and mixins for the documentation.</li>\r\n<li>New class <code>iframe-container</code>. Give to an element that is the parent of an iframe. It will make the iframe responsive.</li>\r\n<li><code>.bg-color-1</code> and <code>.bg-color-2</code> are now standard classes. See classes and mixins for the documentation.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>Changes to comments in code and code organization.</li>\r\n<li>Navbar z-index changed to 2001</li>\r\n<li>Buttons don\'t have buggy styles on active and focus anymore.</li>\r\n<li>Contact Form 7 Submit Buttons now Automatically use <code>color-1</code>.</li>\r\n<li>A featured image for the overall theme has been added. This is the picture that is shown when your go to appearance->themes in the WordPress backend.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/section]','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','4-revision-v1','','','2017-07-13 13:00:54','2017-07-13 18:00:54','',4,'http://sushiexperience.com.test/4-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(2142,4,'2017-07-13 13:35:27','2017-07-13 18:35:27','[section container=\"true\" row=\"true\" full_col=\"true\"]\r\n<div class=\"text-center p15 mb20\" role=\"alert\" style=\"background: RGBA(252, 248, 227, 1.00)\">\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 20px;\">If you add a Shortcode(s) please <b>document it</b>. I created a <a href=\"http://sushiexperience.com.test/shortcodes/documentation-template/\"><b>template for documentation (click me)</b></a> that should make it easy to write some docs. This theme has had <b>multiple</b> updates since 3/10/2017 but the Patch Notes show the theme hasn\'t been updated in months. Anytime a change is made that impacts the theme or gives it added/changed functionality, it needs to be communicated in the Patch Notes and the themes Version needs to be changed (found in functions.php).</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h1>Version [version]</h1>\r\n<h2>PATCH NOTES</h2>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.12.0 - 4/1/2017 - 7/13/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Added new <a href=\"https://www.tippedjs.com/documentation\" target=\"_blank\">Tipped Tooltip</a> plugin. This hasn\'t been converted into a shortcode because of the way the markup needs to by laid out. See the docs on how to use this tooltip.</li>\r\n<li>Updated Bower Components</li>\r\n<li>Brought in latest Font Awesome package.</li>\r\n<li>Created a basic <a href=\"http://sushiexperience.com.test/shortcodes/documentation-template/\">template for documentation</a>. Anytime a new shortcode is added, copy and paste the markup in that page as your starting point.</li>\r\n<li>New \"Example Local Service\" page template added</li>\r\n<li>New \"Example Professional Service\" page template added</li>\r\n<li>New \"Example Product Page\" template added</li>\r\n<li>Social Blocks shortcode added to display stylized social media blocks that tell users to \"Follow\".</li>\r\n<li>Social Sharing Squares shortcode added which share the content on a blog post through the user\'s social media account.</li>\r\n<li>Mobile Top CTA shortcode added along with capability to change buttons in the WYSIWIG editor.</li>\r\n<li>Middle CTA shortcode added that can be fully customized.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.11.1 -  3/10/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>back-up in project folder</li>\r\n<li>Brand New Mobile Menu</li>\r\n<li>The Desktop Menu and Mobile Menu no longer share the same links. You\'ll need to modify the mobile menu in the wordpress backend when you set up the primary menu.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.9 - 3/7/2017 - 3/8/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><code>single-event.php</code> has been rebuilt to better accommodate content and pictures.</li>\r\n<li>New example page \'Home\'</li>\r\n<li>The `gutter` and `gutter_bottom` options from Block Grid have now been added to the gallery shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>All Styles are being enqued the \"right\" way. The bottom of functions.php has this code if your interested on how this is done.</li>\r\n<li>All JavaScript is being enqued the \"right\" way. The bottom of functions.php has this code if your interested on how this is done.</li>\r\n<li>Added CSS prefixes throughout less files.</li>\r\n<li>Same height for event system loop.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.8 - 3/7/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Plugin updates.</li>\r\n<li>Font Weight Classes Added. <code>.fw-{desired-font-weight}</code></li>\r\n<li>The max-width classes bug is gone.</li>\r\n<li>Removed trash ass parallax plugin. </li>\r\n<li>New option <code>full_col</code> for the section shortcode. See the docs for the details.</li>\r\n<li>The <code>placehold</code> shortcode is now for LOREM IPSUM TEXT ONLY. The only new REQUIRED option is <code>lines=\"\"</code> where you feed the number of sentences.</li>\r\n<li>New option for the <code>bc_img</code> shortcode <code>dummy</code>. Since we use a lot of placeholder images, this option gives you the opportunity to feed ONLY THE DIMENSIONS to it and it will output a dummy image based on the dimensions given.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.7 - 3/3/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New file in <code>lib</code> for custom taxonomies. There is a basic function in that file that is commented out that will create a custom taxonomy, but a few of the $args need to change depending on the post type your trying to target with the custom tax.</li>\r\n<li>A lot of the CSS for the navbar has been cleaned up a lot. There was a specificity issue with the styles and sub menu was getting styles from top level links and all sorts of whack other stuff. This is all fixed now.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.6 - 2/24/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>There is a new textblock that will output a form for mailchimp. If you go into <code>mailchimpAjaxHandler.php</code> and pass your API Key and List ID to the proper variables, the form will do the rest for you. Again, this textblock WILL NOT work if you haven\'t set up those variables.</li>\r\n<li>A lot of the animation classes got an upgrade. Smoother, more linear look and they activate earlier instead of having to scroll all the way into the viewport to start the animation</li>\r\n<li>New function in functions.php called <code>build_event_schema($id)</code>. This function is only useable in a PhP file. You need to feed the <code>$post->ID</code> to the function and it will output proper Schema for the event in which you feed the id Event. Schema can be tested <a href=\"https://search.google.com/structured-data/testing-tool\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></li>\r\n<li>There is now a function for signing up subscribers to mailchimp that is easily used with an ajax call to the file.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.5 - 2/21/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[past_event_loop]]</code>. This will output the events that have passed. You need to have the Event module set up in order for this shortcode to execute.</li>\r\n<li>Clean up of some code</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.4 - 2/6/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li> New shortcode <code>[[bc_box]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li> New shortcode <code>[[image_slider]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li>General bug fixes and improvements.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.3 - 1/31/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Parallax is back! You can use this on the section, page banner and page banner large. just set parallax=\"true\" and make sure you give it a background=\"\".</li>\r\n<li>New mobile navbar layout</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.2 - 12/13/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reduced the padding on the contact form on mobile</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[bc_counter]]</code></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.1 - 12/12/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reduced the padding on the contact form on mobile</li>\r\n<li>New helpful script, Pressing <code>SHIFT + Z</code> (on the front end) will toggle the wpadminbar to show and not show.</li>\r\n<li>Board of Directors added.</li>\r\n<li>Style changes to the <a href=\"/blog/\">blog</a> loop</li>\r\n<li>Contact form error styles are better</li>\r\n<li>Set admin columns for Staff and Event posts</li>\r\n<li>single-staff.php added.</li>\r\n<li>LESS code cleanup</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[section_overlay_blend]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[share_links]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li>Changed some default fonts so these docs are nicer looking.</li>\r\n<li>New class - class=\"lh1\". Gives an element line-height: 1;</li>\r\n<li>More Demo Pages Added, see <a href=\"/modules/\">modules</a>.</li>\r\n<li>Few new animation classes created. <code>bc-fade-in-left</code> and <code>bc-fade-in-right</code>. Throw these on any element and it will fade in when scrolled to.</li>\r\n<li>New documentation page for Modules. This page explains how to use the newly implemented systems that take some configuration before starting to use them.</li>\r\n<li>New javascript file added called theme.js. This file was added to house all the javascript that is necessary for the theme to work properly. The main.js file was getting really crowded and it should now be used for website specific scripts.</li>\r\n<li>Bye Steph, your not a user anymore. Pwned.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode social_inline. See the docs for the details.</li>\r\n<li>New class text-fade added to the theme. Give to a piece of text, header, etc. and it will fade in when scrolled to.</li>\r\n<li>the img_overlay shortcode has been modified to look and work cleaner.</li>\r\n<li>The img shortcode has been modified. See the docs for all the new options.</li>\r\n<li>Change made to the header. We kept the Columns but just pulled the padding from them, so everything should work more fluidly.</li>\r\n<li>Admin Columns Pro with the ACF add-on has been added to the plugins.</li>\r\n<li>The staff system that was first implemented on UAP has been added to the theme. To get everything going, you need to uncomment the custom post type staff and use the <code>bc_staff_grid</code> shortcode. All the styles and javascript are ready to go. Styles can be found in textblocks-and-shortcodes.</li>\r\n<li>Food Menu system added to the theme. To get it going, make a page and set the template to Featured Menu and your good to go. Styles can be found in textblocks-shortcodes less file.</li>\r\n<li>Hours option added to Schema, Address Loop and Mobile Location Conversion shortcodes.</li>\r\n<li>Caption option added to the gallery shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>Custom Role code updated to have further control over custom roles.</li>\r\n<li>Event System added. To set up, active custom posts types in functions and the event post is already built into the custom post file. You also need to set the event custom fields to match post type event. Styles for the event card and single event are found in textblocks-shortcodes.less</li>\r\n<li>ALL bower components (such as bootstrap, slick, jquery, matchHeight, FontAwesome, etc) have all been updated to their most recent version available as of 11/16/2016.</li>\r\n<li>Libraries and Frameworks in Global Content has been deprecated, we\'re just going to bring in all the Bower Components.</li>\r\n<li>Business Hours added to the Global Content page, with the address and such.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed a bug with Gallery shortcode where the image wasn\'t responsive.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.17 - 11/8/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A 768x768 placeholder image has been added to the media uploads. We always seem to need placeholder post images and placeholder staff images, etc, so this will be nice to have in the media folder.</li>\r\n<li>There are no longer different footer layouts. The layout just lives in footer.php now</li>\r\n<li><code>mobile-text-center</code> class has been added to center on viewports under 768px.</li>\r\n<li>Change to the mobile nav dropdown links. There was an issue that if there were too many links, you weren\'t able to scroll down the mobile nav links, it would scroll the page behind it. That has now been fixed.</li>\r\n<li>search function now available for mobile. The variable to toggle it is in header.php</li>\r\n<li>the shortcode <code>single_location_address</code> has been deprecated. Just use <code>schema</code> instead.</li>\r\n<li>new option for the address_attr shortcode - <code>link</code>. See the <a href=\"/shortcodes/address-attribute/\">docs</a> for how to use it. </li>\r\n<li>container-fluid option now available for the section shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed a bug with Gallery shortcode where the image wasn\'t responsive.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.16 - 11/2/2016 - 11/3/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Breadcrumbs now have schema</li>\r\n<li>Search function now a part of the theme.</li>\r\n<li>Visual editor has been disabled for ALL USERS. (code for this is found in /lib/setup.php)</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The buttons for the mobile footer have been re-vamped to fit better.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.15 - 10/26/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Drop down menu for mobile is now a lot easier to touch on a mobile device, as well as having a new look.</a>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Changed some default accordion styles.</li>\r\n<li>Removed the formula we previously had for calculating height of logo for the navbar and spacing etc. It just wasn\'t consistent enough and all depended on what the companies logo looks like.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.14 - 10/21/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New classes added to change text color to the LESS variables color-1 and color-2</li>\r\n<li>Removed Stellar JS (the parallax plugin). It was way too buggy. We will need to investigate a new parallax option. This means that you can no longer use the \'parallax\' option for some of our shortcodes. Avoid using that option until further notice.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed bug with Block Grid that was causing it to always go 2 across on mobile.</li>\r\n<li>Removed some Text Blocks we never use.</li>\r\n<li>Section Split has been fixed to work better on all viewports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.13 - 09/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Minor fix to the video bg plugin.</li>\r\n<li>Big improvement to the <a href=\"/blog/\">blog</a> template.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The mobile logo and desktop logo for the navbar are now variables. Just plug in the path/to/file and it\'ll get injected for you.</li>\r\n<li>Changes visually to the sidebar with form textblock.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.12 - 09/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>So yea... section_video is gone. But fear not! We just made it easier to execute a video background. It is now built into the regular <code>section</code> shortcode. Peep the docs.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.11 - 09/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><code>underlay</code> option had been added to the <code>section</code> shortcode. Peep the docs for the 411.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.10 - 09/21/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><code>target</code> option added to bc_btn shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>New legitness section_video. Find out more about this badass shortcode [anchor href=\"http://sushiexperience.com.test/shortcodes/section-video/\" content=\"here\"].</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.9 - 09/15/2016 - 09/16/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Theme now supports sub-sub menu.</li>\r\n<li>Block grid has a new options <code>gutter</code>, <code>gutter_lower</code>, and <code>animate</code> . See the docs for more information.</li>\r\n<li>Icon Schema has been deprecated.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode Schema.</li>\r\n<li>Theme now supports companies with Fax numbers.</li>\r\n<li>BXSlider has been deprecated to make the switch to Slick Carousel. <a href=\"https://kenwheeler.github.io/slick/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link-color-2\">Slick Docs</a></li>\r\n<li>New shortcodes for slider. See the docs for more info.</a></li>\r\n<li>Slider, match height, and waypoints are no longer optional plugins. The theme relies on these too often so they are by default included in the theme.</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.8 - 09/12/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New class has been added <code>.section-split</code>. Using this class relies on your columns following a certain layout. See the docs for more info!</li>\r\n<li>A brand new page template has been added to the theme. This makes building over conversion pages (content left, sidebar right) a lot faster and it is basically automated now. When you create a new page, change the template to Sub Page Template and the rest is done for you. [anchor href=\"/page-template-sub-page/\" content=\"Here\"] is what the page looks like. If at any point you want to make edits to the template, just edit the <code>template-sub-page.php</code> file.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.7 - 09/09/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Stellar.JS has been added to the theme. This is not an optional plugin, it needs to always stay in the theme. Stellar allows parallax backgrounds. There is a new option on the section shortcode and the page_banner_large shortcode. Simply just set parallax=\"true\" and boom, you\'ll have parallax. Docs have been updated with new options.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.6 - 08/30/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New shortcode img_overlay</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode team_block</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode g_map</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.5 - 08/25/2016 - 08/29/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The excerpt read character length is now set to 20 characters. To change this, you can go into setup.php.</li>\r\n<li>The excerpt read more has been changed from WP\'s default [...] to just simply ... </li>\r\n<li>New tracking options for button and anchor.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode img_flex.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode page_banner_flex. </li>\r\n<li>Formulated mobile navbar calculations. </li>\r\n<li>The issue with nesting a col shortcode inside another col shortcode has been address. In WordPress you cannot nest shortcodes that use the same name, so nesting our column shortcode needed a work-around. If you want to nest a col inside another col you need to use <code>col_nested</code> for the nested columns. It works and has the same options as the col shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>The contact page form now has color validation. Red inset shadow gets added if req field is skipped over and green inset shadow is added if it has a value.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>ul\'s and ol\'s now have default 25px padding left and 10px margin bottom. Use <code>class=\"list-unstyled\"</code> if you don\'t want any styles to your list.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.4 - 08/23/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>New contact page form layout. There are by default two different forms. One that has labels and one that does not and uses placeholders instead.</li>\r\n<li>You can now toggle the admin bar on and off. This is especially useful when in development. Just uncomment the show_admin_bar(false) function to hide the admin bar.</li>\r\n<li>New LESS Mixin <code>placeholder-color(@color);</code>. See documentation for details.</li>\r\n<li>New classes <code>link-blend</code> <code>text-right</code> <code>text-left</code>. See documentation for more details.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>Big fixes to navbar active page. All the active styles now apply correctly.</li>\r\n<li>Fix to last of type link in navbar. There was a bug were it was giving styles we didn\'t want to the sub menu.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.3 - 08/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>Footer, Mobile Nav, Topbar and more use address attributes from Global Content to populate contact data.</li>\r\n<li>Bug fix to the placehold shortcode where it would return one extra sentence then what you asked for.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.2 - 08/19/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>New grid layout on navbar & logo display block.</li>\r\n<li>No padding-right on last-of-type navbar link. (css in !important on this rule)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.1 - 08/18/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>If an anchor tag has <code>#</code> as the href attribute, it will no longer make the page jump or add \"#\" to the end of the URL. It will simply do nothing at all.</li>\r\n<li>Login page now has the BrandCoders logo and clicking that logo now takes you to brandcoders.com. If you want to change these settings, you can find them in <code>lib/setup.php</code>.</li>\r\n<li>A default \'Thank You\' page has been implemented into theme and is already linked up to default contact form.</li>\r\n<li>The default buttons paddings have been increased on all sizes. They have <a href=\"https://foundation.zurb.com/sites/docs/v/5.5.3/components/buttons.html#button-sizing\" target=\"_blank\">foundations</a> sizes. They are a pretty good standard.</li>\r\n<li>New max width classes have been implemented into the theme. See classes and mixins for the documentation.</li>\r\n<li>New class <code>iframe-container</code>. Give to an element that is the parent of an iframe. It will make the iframe responsive.</li>\r\n<li><code>.bg-color-1</code> and <code>.bg-color-2</code> are now standard classes. See classes and mixins for the documentation.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>Changes to comments in code and code organization.</li>\r\n<li>Navbar z-index changed to 2001</li>\r\n<li>Buttons don\'t have buggy styles on active and focus anymore.</li>\r\n<li>Contact Form 7 Submit Buttons now Automatically use <code>color-1</code>.</li>\r\n<li>A featured image for the overall theme has been added. This is the picture that is shown when your go to appearance->themes in the WordPress backend.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/section]','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','4-revision-v1','','','2017-07-13 13:35:27','2017-07-13 18:35:27','',4,'http://sushiexperience.com.test/4-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(2155,4,'2017-07-13 13:44:54','2017-07-13 18:44:54','[section container=\"true\" row=\"true\" full_col=\"true\"]\r\n<div class=\"text-center p15 mb20\" role=\"alert\" style=\"background: RGBA(252, 248, 227, 1.00)\">\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 20px;\">If you add a Shortcode(s) please <b>document it</b>. I created a <a href=\"http://sushiexperience.com.test/shortcodes/documentation-template/\"><b>template for documentation (click me)</b></a> that should make it easy to write some docs. This theme has had <b>multiple</b> updates since 3/10/2017 but the Patch Notes show the theme hasn\'t been updated in months. Anytime a change is made that impacts the theme or gives it added/changed functionality, it needs to be communicated in the Patch Notes and the themes Version needs to be changed (found in functions.php).</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h1>Version [version]</h1>\r\n<h2>PATCH NOTES</h2>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.12.0 - 4/1/2017 - 7/13/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Added new <a href=\"https://www.tippedjs.com/documentation\" target=\"_blank\">Tipped Tooltip</a> plugin. This hasn\'t been converted into a shortcode because of the way the markup needs to by laid out. See the <a href=\"/classes-and-mixins/tooltips/\">our docs</a> on how to use this tooltip.</li>\r\n<li>Updated Bower Components</li>\r\n<li>Brought in latest Font Awesome package.</li>\r\n<li>Created a basic <a href=\"http://sushiexperience.com.test/shortcodes/documentation-template/\">template for documentation</a>. Anytime a new shortcode is added, copy and paste the markup in that page as your starting point.</li>\r\n<li>New \"Example Local Service\" page template added</li>\r\n<li>New \"Example Professional Service\" page template added</li>\r\n<li>New \"Example Product Page\" template added</li>\r\n<li>Social Blocks shortcode added to display stylized social media blocks that tell users to \"Follow\".</li>\r\n<li>Social Sharing Squares shortcode added which share the content on a blog post through the user\'s social media account.</li>\r\n<li>Mobile Top CTA shortcode added along with capability to change buttons in the WYSIWIG editor.</li>\r\n<li>Middle CTA shortcode added that can be fully customized.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.11.1 -  3/10/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>back-up in project folder</li>\r\n<li>Brand New Mobile Menu</li>\r\n<li>The Desktop Menu and Mobile Menu no longer share the same links. You\'ll need to modify the mobile menu in the wordpress backend when you set up the primary menu.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.9 - 3/7/2017 - 3/8/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><code>single-event.php</code> has been rebuilt to better accommodate content and pictures.</li>\r\n<li>New example page \'Home\'</li>\r\n<li>The `gutter` and `gutter_bottom` options from Block Grid have now been added to the gallery shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>All Styles are being enqued the \"right\" way. The bottom of functions.php has this code if your interested on how this is done.</li>\r\n<li>All JavaScript is being enqued the \"right\" way. The bottom of functions.php has this code if your interested on how this is done.</li>\r\n<li>Added CSS prefixes throughout less files.</li>\r\n<li>Same height for event system loop.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.8 - 3/7/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Plugin updates.</li>\r\n<li>Font Weight Classes Added. <code>.fw-{desired-font-weight}</code></li>\r\n<li>The max-width classes bug is gone.</li>\r\n<li>Removed trash ass parallax plugin. </li>\r\n<li>New option <code>full_col</code> for the section shortcode. See the docs for the details.</li>\r\n<li>The <code>placehold</code> shortcode is now for LOREM IPSUM TEXT ONLY. The only new REQUIRED option is <code>lines=\"\"</code> where you feed the number of sentences.</li>\r\n<li>New option for the <code>bc_img</code> shortcode <code>dummy</code>. Since we use a lot of placeholder images, this option gives you the opportunity to feed ONLY THE DIMENSIONS to it and it will output a dummy image based on the dimensions given.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.7 - 3/3/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New file in <code>lib</code> for custom taxonomies. There is a basic function in that file that is commented out that will create a custom taxonomy, but a few of the $args need to change depending on the post type your trying to target with the custom tax.</li>\r\n<li>A lot of the CSS for the navbar has been cleaned up a lot. There was a specificity issue with the styles and sub menu was getting styles from top level links and all sorts of whack other stuff. This is all fixed now.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.6 - 2/24/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>There is a new textblock that will output a form for mailchimp. If you go into <code>mailchimpAjaxHandler.php</code> and pass your API Key and List ID to the proper variables, the form will do the rest for you. Again, this textblock WILL NOT work if you haven\'t set up those variables.</li>\r\n<li>A lot of the animation classes got an upgrade. Smoother, more linear look and they activate earlier instead of having to scroll all the way into the viewport to start the animation</li>\r\n<li>New function in functions.php called <code>build_event_schema($id)</code>. This function is only useable in a PhP file. You need to feed the <code>$post->ID</code> to the function and it will output proper Schema for the event in which you feed the id Event. Schema can be tested <a href=\"https://search.google.com/structured-data/testing-tool\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></li>\r\n<li>There is now a function for signing up subscribers to mailchimp that is easily used with an ajax call to the file.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.5 - 2/21/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[past_event_loop]]</code>. This will output the events that have passed. You need to have the Event module set up in order for this shortcode to execute.</li>\r\n<li>Clean up of some code</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.4 - 2/6/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li> New shortcode <code>[[bc_box]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li> New shortcode <code>[[image_slider]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li>General bug fixes and improvements.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.3 - 1/31/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Parallax is back! You can use this on the section, page banner and page banner large. just set parallax=\"true\" and make sure you give it a background=\"\".</li>\r\n<li>New mobile navbar layout</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.2 - 12/13/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reduced the padding on the contact form on mobile</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[bc_counter]]</code></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.1 - 12/12/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reduced the padding on the contact form on mobile</li>\r\n<li>New helpful script, Pressing <code>SHIFT + Z</code> (on the front end) will toggle the wpadminbar to show and not show.</li>\r\n<li>Board of Directors added.</li>\r\n<li>Style changes to the <a href=\"/blog/\">blog</a> loop</li>\r\n<li>Contact form error styles are better</li>\r\n<li>Set admin columns for Staff and Event posts</li>\r\n<li>single-staff.php added.</li>\r\n<li>LESS code cleanup</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[section_overlay_blend]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[share_links]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li>Changed some default fonts so these docs are nicer looking.</li>\r\n<li>New class - class=\"lh1\". Gives an element line-height: 1;</li>\r\n<li>More Demo Pages Added, see <a href=\"/modules/\">modules</a>.</li>\r\n<li>Few new animation classes created. <code>bc-fade-in-left</code> and <code>bc-fade-in-right</code>. Throw these on any element and it will fade in when scrolled to.</li>\r\n<li>New documentation page for Modules. This page explains how to use the newly implemented systems that take some configuration before starting to use them.</li>\r\n<li>New javascript file added called theme.js. This file was added to house all the javascript that is necessary for the theme to work properly. The main.js file was getting really crowded and it should now be used for website specific scripts.</li>\r\n<li>Bye Steph, your not a user anymore. Pwned.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode social_inline. See the docs for the details.</li>\r\n<li>New class text-fade added to the theme. Give to a piece of text, header, etc. and it will fade in when scrolled to.</li>\r\n<li>the img_overlay shortcode has been modified to look and work cleaner.</li>\r\n<li>The img shortcode has been modified. See the docs for all the new options.</li>\r\n<li>Change made to the header. We kept the Columns but just pulled the padding from them, so everything should work more fluidly.</li>\r\n<li>Admin Columns Pro with the ACF add-on has been added to the plugins.</li>\r\n<li>The staff system that was first implemented on UAP has been added to the theme. To get everything going, you need to uncomment the custom post type staff and use the <code>bc_staff_grid</code> shortcode. All the styles and javascript are ready to go. Styles can be found in textblocks-and-shortcodes.</li>\r\n<li>Food Menu system added to the theme. To get it going, make a page and set the template to Featured Menu and your good to go. Styles can be found in textblocks-shortcodes less file.</li>\r\n<li>Hours option added to Schema, Address Loop and Mobile Location Conversion shortcodes.</li>\r\n<li>Caption option added to the gallery shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>Custom Role code updated to have further control over custom roles.</li>\r\n<li>Event System added. To set up, active custom posts types in functions and the event post is already built into the custom post file. You also need to set the event custom fields to match post type event. Styles for the event card and single event are found in textblocks-shortcodes.less</li>\r\n<li>ALL bower components (such as bootstrap, slick, jquery, matchHeight, FontAwesome, etc) have all been updated to their most recent version available as of 11/16/2016.</li>\r\n<li>Libraries and Frameworks in Global Content has been deprecated, we\'re just going to bring in all the Bower Components.</li>\r\n<li>Business Hours added to the Global Content page, with the address and such.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed a bug with Gallery shortcode where the image wasn\'t responsive.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.17 - 11/8/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A 768x768 placeholder image has been added to the media uploads. We always seem to need placeholder post images and placeholder staff images, etc, so this will be nice to have in the media folder.</li>\r\n<li>There are no longer different footer layouts. The layout just lives in footer.php now</li>\r\n<li><code>mobile-text-center</code> class has been added to center on viewports under 768px.</li>\r\n<li>Change to the mobile nav dropdown links. There was an issue that if there were too many links, you weren\'t able to scroll down the mobile nav links, it would scroll the page behind it. That has now been fixed.</li>\r\n<li>search function now available for mobile. The variable to toggle it is in header.php</li>\r\n<li>the shortcode <code>single_location_address</code> has been deprecated. Just use <code>schema</code> instead.</li>\r\n<li>new option for the address_attr shortcode - <code>link</code>. See the <a href=\"/shortcodes/address-attribute/\">docs</a> for how to use it. </li>\r\n<li>container-fluid option now available for the section shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed a bug with Gallery shortcode where the image wasn\'t responsive.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.16 - 11/2/2016 - 11/3/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Breadcrumbs now have schema</li>\r\n<li>Search function now a part of the theme.</li>\r\n<li>Visual editor has been disabled for ALL USERS. (code for this is found in /lib/setup.php)</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The buttons for the mobile footer have been re-vamped to fit better.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.15 - 10/26/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Drop down menu for mobile is now a lot easier to touch on a mobile device, as well as having a new look.</a>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Changed some default accordion styles.</li>\r\n<li>Removed the formula we previously had for calculating height of logo for the navbar and spacing etc. It just wasn\'t consistent enough and all depended on what the companies logo looks like.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.14 - 10/21/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New classes added to change text color to the LESS variables color-1 and color-2</li>\r\n<li>Removed Stellar JS (the parallax plugin). It was way too buggy. We will need to investigate a new parallax option. This means that you can no longer use the \'parallax\' option for some of our shortcodes. Avoid using that option until further notice.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed bug with Block Grid that was causing it to always go 2 across on mobile.</li>\r\n<li>Removed some Text Blocks we never use.</li>\r\n<li>Section Split has been fixed to work better on all viewports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.13 - 09/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Minor fix to the video bg plugin.</li>\r\n<li>Big improvement to the <a href=\"/blog/\">blog</a> template.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The mobile logo and desktop logo for the navbar are now variables. Just plug in the path/to/file and it\'ll get injected for you.</li>\r\n<li>Changes visually to the sidebar with form textblock.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.12 - 09/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>So yea... section_video is gone. But fear not! We just made it easier to execute a video background. It is now built into the regular <code>section</code> shortcode. Peep the docs.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.11 - 09/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><code>underlay</code> option had been added to the <code>section</code> shortcode. Peep the docs for the 411.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.10 - 09/21/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><code>target</code> option added to bc_btn shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>New legitness section_video. Find out more about this badass shortcode [anchor href=\"http://sushiexperience.com.test/shortcodes/section-video/\" content=\"here\"].</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.9 - 09/15/2016 - 09/16/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Theme now supports sub-sub menu.</li>\r\n<li>Block grid has a new options <code>gutter</code>, <code>gutter_lower</code>, and <code>animate</code> . See the docs for more information.</li>\r\n<li>Icon Schema has been deprecated.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode Schema.</li>\r\n<li>Theme now supports companies with Fax numbers.</li>\r\n<li>BXSlider has been deprecated to make the switch to Slick Carousel. <a href=\"https://kenwheeler.github.io/slick/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link-color-2\">Slick Docs</a></li>\r\n<li>New shortcodes for slider. See the docs for more info.</a></li>\r\n<li>Slider, match height, and waypoints are no longer optional plugins. The theme relies on these too often so they are by default included in the theme.</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.8 - 09/12/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New class has been added <code>.section-split</code>. Using this class relies on your columns following a certain layout. See the docs for more info!</li>\r\n<li>A brand new page template has been added to the theme. This makes building over conversion pages (content left, sidebar right) a lot faster and it is basically automated now. When you create a new page, change the template to Sub Page Template and the rest is done for you. [anchor href=\"/page-template-sub-page/\" content=\"Here\"] is what the page looks like. If at any point you want to make edits to the template, just edit the <code>template-sub-page.php</code> file.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.7 - 09/09/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Stellar.JS has been added to the theme. This is not an optional plugin, it needs to always stay in the theme. Stellar allows parallax backgrounds. There is a new option on the section shortcode and the page_banner_large shortcode. Simply just set parallax=\"true\" and boom, you\'ll have parallax. Docs have been updated with new options.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.6 - 08/30/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New shortcode img_overlay</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode team_block</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode g_map</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.5 - 08/25/2016 - 08/29/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The excerpt read character length is now set to 20 characters. To change this, you can go into setup.php.</li>\r\n<li>The excerpt read more has been changed from WP\'s default [...] to just simply ... </li>\r\n<li>New tracking options for button and anchor.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode img_flex.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode page_banner_flex. </li>\r\n<li>Formulated mobile navbar calculations. </li>\r\n<li>The issue with nesting a col shortcode inside another col shortcode has been address. In WordPress you cannot nest shortcodes that use the same name, so nesting our column shortcode needed a work-around. If you want to nest a col inside another col you need to use <code>col_nested</code> for the nested columns. It works and has the same options as the col shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>The contact page form now has color validation. Red inset shadow gets added if req field is skipped over and green inset shadow is added if it has a value.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>ul\'s and ol\'s now have default 25px padding left and 10px margin bottom. Use <code>class=\"list-unstyled\"</code> if you don\'t want any styles to your list.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.4 - 08/23/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>New contact page form layout. There are by default two different forms. One that has labels and one that does not and uses placeholders instead.</li>\r\n<li>You can now toggle the admin bar on and off. This is especially useful when in development. Just uncomment the show_admin_bar(false) function to hide the admin bar.</li>\r\n<li>New LESS Mixin <code>placeholder-color(@color);</code>. See documentation for details.</li>\r\n<li>New classes <code>link-blend</code> <code>text-right</code> <code>text-left</code>. See documentation for more details.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>Big fixes to navbar active page. All the active styles now apply correctly.</li>\r\n<li>Fix to last of type link in navbar. There was a bug were it was giving styles we didn\'t want to the sub menu.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.3 - 08/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>Footer, Mobile Nav, Topbar and more use address attributes from Global Content to populate contact data.</li>\r\n<li>Bug fix to the placehold shortcode where it would return one extra sentence then what you asked for.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.2 - 08/19/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>New grid layout on navbar & logo display block.</li>\r\n<li>No padding-right on last-of-type navbar link. (css in !important on this rule)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.1 - 08/18/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>If an anchor tag has <code>#</code> as the href attribute, it will no longer make the page jump or add \"#\" to the end of the URL. It will simply do nothing at all.</li>\r\n<li>Login page now has the BrandCoders logo and clicking that logo now takes you to brandcoders.com. If you want to change these settings, you can find them in <code>lib/setup.php</code>.</li>\r\n<li>A default \'Thank You\' page has been implemented into theme and is already linked up to default contact form.</li>\r\n<li>The default buttons paddings have been increased on all sizes. They have <a href=\"https://foundation.zurb.com/sites/docs/v/5.5.3/components/buttons.html#button-sizing\" target=\"_blank\">foundations</a> sizes. They are a pretty good standard.</li>\r\n<li>New max width classes have been implemented into the theme. See classes and mixins for the documentation.</li>\r\n<li>New class <code>iframe-container</code>. Give to an element that is the parent of an iframe. It will make the iframe responsive.</li>\r\n<li><code>.bg-color-1</code> and <code>.bg-color-2</code> are now standard classes. See classes and mixins for the documentation.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>Changes to comments in code and code organization.</li>\r\n<li>Navbar z-index changed to 2001</li>\r\n<li>Buttons don\'t have buggy styles on active and focus anymore.</li>\r\n<li>Contact Form 7 Submit Buttons now Automatically use <code>color-1</code>.</li>\r\n<li>A featured image for the overall theme has been added. This is the picture that is shown when your go to appearance->themes in the WordPress backend.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/section]','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','4-revision-v1','','','2017-07-13 13:44:54','2017-07-13 18:44:54','',4,'http://sushiexperience.com.test/4-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(2156,4,'2017-07-13 14:15:01','2017-07-13 19:15:01','[section container=\"true\" row=\"true\" full_col=\"true\"]\r\n<div class=\"text-center p15 mb20\" role=\"alert\" style=\"background: RGBA(252, 248, 227, 1.00)\">\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 20px;\">If you add a Shortcode(s) please <b>document it</b>. I created a <a href=\"http://sushiexperience.com.test/shortcodes/documentation-template/\"><b>template for documentation (click me)</b></a> that should make it easy to write some docs. This theme has had <b>multiple</b> updates since 3/10/2017 but the Patch Notes show the theme hasn\'t been updated in months. Anytime a change is made that impacts the theme or gives it added/changed functionality, it needs to be communicated in the Patch Notes and the themes Version needs to be changed (found in functions.php).</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h1>Version [version]</h1>\r\n<h2>PATCH NOTES</h2>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.12.0 - 4/1/2017 - 7/13/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Changes to Accordion styles.</li>\r\n<li>Added new <a href=\"https://www.tippedjs.com/documentation\" target=\"_blank\">Tipped Tooltip</a> plugin. This hasn\'t been converted into a shortcode because of the way the markup needs to by laid out. See the <a href=\"/classes-and-mixins/tooltips/\">our docs</a> on how to use this tooltip.</li>\r\n<li>Updated Bower Components</li>\r\n<li>Brought in latest Font Awesome package.</li>\r\n<li>Created a basic <a href=\"http://sushiexperience.com.test/shortcodes/documentation-template/\">template for documentation</a>. Anytime a new shortcode is added, copy and paste the markup in that page as your starting point.</li>\r\n<li>New \"Example Local Service\" page template added</li>\r\n<li>New \"Example Professional Service\" page template added</li>\r\n<li>New \"Example Product Page\" template added</li>\r\n<li>Social Blocks shortcode added to display stylized social media blocks that tell users to \"Follow\".</li>\r\n<li>Social Sharing Squares shortcode added which share the content on a blog post through the user\'s social media account.</li>\r\n<li>Mobile Top CTA shortcode added along with capability to change buttons in the WYSIWIG editor.</li>\r\n<li>Middle CTA shortcode added that can be fully customized.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.11.1 -  3/10/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>back-up in project folder</li>\r\n<li>Brand New Mobile Menu</li>\r\n<li>The Desktop Menu and Mobile Menu no longer share the same links. You\'ll need to modify the mobile menu in the wordpress backend when you set up the primary menu.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.9 - 3/7/2017 - 3/8/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><code>single-event.php</code> has been rebuilt to better accommodate content and pictures.</li>\r\n<li>New example page \'Home\'</li>\r\n<li>The `gutter` and `gutter_bottom` options from Block Grid have now been added to the gallery shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>All Styles are being enqued the \"right\" way. The bottom of functions.php has this code if your interested on how this is done.</li>\r\n<li>All JavaScript is being enqued the \"right\" way. The bottom of functions.php has this code if your interested on how this is done.</li>\r\n<li>Added CSS prefixes throughout less files.</li>\r\n<li>Same height for event system loop.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.8 - 3/7/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Plugin updates.</li>\r\n<li>Font Weight Classes Added. <code>.fw-{desired-font-weight}</code></li>\r\n<li>The max-width classes bug is gone.</li>\r\n<li>Removed trash ass parallax plugin. </li>\r\n<li>New option <code>full_col</code> for the section shortcode. See the docs for the details.</li>\r\n<li>The <code>placehold</code> shortcode is now for LOREM IPSUM TEXT ONLY. The only new REQUIRED option is <code>lines=\"\"</code> where you feed the number of sentences.</li>\r\n<li>New option for the <code>bc_img</code> shortcode <code>dummy</code>. Since we use a lot of placeholder images, this option gives you the opportunity to feed ONLY THE DIMENSIONS to it and it will output a dummy image based on the dimensions given.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.7 - 3/3/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New file in <code>lib</code> for custom taxonomies. There is a basic function in that file that is commented out that will create a custom taxonomy, but a few of the $args need to change depending on the post type your trying to target with the custom tax.</li>\r\n<li>A lot of the CSS for the navbar has been cleaned up a lot. There was a specificity issue with the styles and sub menu was getting styles from top level links and all sorts of whack other stuff. This is all fixed now.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.6 - 2/24/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>There is a new textblock that will output a form for mailchimp. If you go into <code>mailchimpAjaxHandler.php</code> and pass your API Key and List ID to the proper variables, the form will do the rest for you. Again, this textblock WILL NOT work if you haven\'t set up those variables.</li>\r\n<li>A lot of the animation classes got an upgrade. Smoother, more linear look and they activate earlier instead of having to scroll all the way into the viewport to start the animation</li>\r\n<li>New function in functions.php called <code>build_event_schema($id)</code>. This function is only useable in a PhP file. You need to feed the <code>$post->ID</code> to the function and it will output proper Schema for the event in which you feed the id Event. Schema can be tested <a href=\"https://search.google.com/structured-data/testing-tool\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></li>\r\n<li>There is now a function for signing up subscribers to mailchimp that is easily used with an ajax call to the file.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.5 - 2/21/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[past_event_loop]]</code>. This will output the events that have passed. You need to have the Event module set up in order for this shortcode to execute.</li>\r\n<li>Clean up of some code</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.4 - 2/6/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li> New shortcode <code>[[bc_box]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li> New shortcode <code>[[image_slider]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li>General bug fixes and improvements.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.3 - 1/31/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Parallax is back! You can use this on the section, page banner and page banner large. just set parallax=\"true\" and make sure you give it a background=\"\".</li>\r\n<li>New mobile navbar layout</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.2 - 12/13/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reduced the padding on the contact form on mobile</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[bc_counter]]</code></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.1 - 12/12/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reduced the padding on the contact form on mobile</li>\r\n<li>New helpful script, Pressing <code>SHIFT + Z</code> (on the front end) will toggle the wpadminbar to show and not show.</li>\r\n<li>Board of Directors added.</li>\r\n<li>Style changes to the <a href=\"/blog/\">blog</a> loop</li>\r\n<li>Contact form error styles are better</li>\r\n<li>Set admin columns for Staff and Event posts</li>\r\n<li>single-staff.php added.</li>\r\n<li>LESS code cleanup</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[section_overlay_blend]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[share_links]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li>Changed some default fonts so these docs are nicer looking.</li>\r\n<li>New class - class=\"lh1\". Gives an element line-height: 1;</li>\r\n<li>More Demo Pages Added, see <a href=\"/modules/\">modules</a>.</li>\r\n<li>Few new animation classes created. <code>bc-fade-in-left</code> and <code>bc-fade-in-right</code>. Throw these on any element and it will fade in when scrolled to.</li>\r\n<li>New documentation page for Modules. This page explains how to use the newly implemented systems that take some configuration before starting to use them.</li>\r\n<li>New javascript file added called theme.js. This file was added to house all the javascript that is necessary for the theme to work properly. The main.js file was getting really crowded and it should now be used for website specific scripts.</li>\r\n<li>Bye Steph, your not a user anymore. Pwned.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode social_inline. See the docs for the details.</li>\r\n<li>New class text-fade added to the theme. Give to a piece of text, header, etc. and it will fade in when scrolled to.</li>\r\n<li>the img_overlay shortcode has been modified to look and work cleaner.</li>\r\n<li>The img shortcode has been modified. See the docs for all the new options.</li>\r\n<li>Change made to the header. We kept the Columns but just pulled the padding from them, so everything should work more fluidly.</li>\r\n<li>Admin Columns Pro with the ACF add-on has been added to the plugins.</li>\r\n<li>The staff system that was first implemented on UAP has been added to the theme. To get everything going, you need to uncomment the custom post type staff and use the <code>bc_staff_grid</code> shortcode. All the styles and javascript are ready to go. Styles can be found in textblocks-and-shortcodes.</li>\r\n<li>Food Menu system added to the theme. To get it going, make a page and set the template to Featured Menu and your good to go. Styles can be found in textblocks-shortcodes less file.</li>\r\n<li>Hours option added to Schema, Address Loop and Mobile Location Conversion shortcodes.</li>\r\n<li>Caption option added to the gallery shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>Custom Role code updated to have further control over custom roles.</li>\r\n<li>Event System added. To set up, active custom posts types in functions and the event post is already built into the custom post file. You also need to set the event custom fields to match post type event. Styles for the event card and single event are found in textblocks-shortcodes.less</li>\r\n<li>ALL bower components (such as bootstrap, slick, jquery, matchHeight, FontAwesome, etc) have all been updated to their most recent version available as of 11/16/2016.</li>\r\n<li>Libraries and Frameworks in Global Content has been deprecated, we\'re just going to bring in all the Bower Components.</li>\r\n<li>Business Hours added to the Global Content page, with the address and such.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed a bug with Gallery shortcode where the image wasn\'t responsive.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.17 - 11/8/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A 768x768 placeholder image has been added to the media uploads. We always seem to need placeholder post images and placeholder staff images, etc, so this will be nice to have in the media folder.</li>\r\n<li>There are no longer different footer layouts. The layout just lives in footer.php now</li>\r\n<li><code>mobile-text-center</code> class has been added to center on viewports under 768px.</li>\r\n<li>Change to the mobile nav dropdown links. There was an issue that if there were too many links, you weren\'t able to scroll down the mobile nav links, it would scroll the page behind it. That has now been fixed.</li>\r\n<li>search function now available for mobile. The variable to toggle it is in header.php</li>\r\n<li>the shortcode <code>single_location_address</code> has been deprecated. Just use <code>schema</code> instead.</li>\r\n<li>new option for the address_attr shortcode - <code>link</code>. See the <a href=\"/shortcodes/address-attribute/\">docs</a> for how to use it. </li>\r\n<li>container-fluid option now available for the section shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed a bug with Gallery shortcode where the image wasn\'t responsive.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.16 - 11/2/2016 - 11/3/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Breadcrumbs now have schema</li>\r\n<li>Search function now a part of the theme.</li>\r\n<li>Visual editor has been disabled for ALL USERS. (code for this is found in /lib/setup.php)</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The buttons for the mobile footer have been re-vamped to fit better.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.15 - 10/26/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Drop down menu for mobile is now a lot easier to touch on a mobile device, as well as having a new look.</a>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Changed some default accordion styles.</li>\r\n<li>Removed the formula we previously had for calculating height of logo for the navbar and spacing etc. It just wasn\'t consistent enough and all depended on what the companies logo looks like.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.14 - 10/21/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New classes added to change text color to the LESS variables color-1 and color-2</li>\r\n<li>Removed Stellar JS (the parallax plugin). It was way too buggy. We will need to investigate a new parallax option. This means that you can no longer use the \'parallax\' option for some of our shortcodes. Avoid using that option until further notice.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed bug with Block Grid that was causing it to always go 2 across on mobile.</li>\r\n<li>Removed some Text Blocks we never use.</li>\r\n<li>Section Split has been fixed to work better on all viewports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.13 - 09/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Minor fix to the video bg plugin.</li>\r\n<li>Big improvement to the <a href=\"/blog/\">blog</a> template.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The mobile logo and desktop logo for the navbar are now variables. Just plug in the path/to/file and it\'ll get injected for you.</li>\r\n<li>Changes visually to the sidebar with form textblock.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.12 - 09/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>So yea... section_video is gone. But fear not! We just made it easier to execute a video background. It is now built into the regular <code>section</code> shortcode. Peep the docs.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.11 - 09/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><code>underlay</code> option had been added to the <code>section</code> shortcode. Peep the docs for the 411.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.10 - 09/21/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><code>target</code> option added to bc_btn shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>New legitness section_video. Find out more about this badass shortcode [anchor href=\"http://sushiexperience.com.test/shortcodes/section-video/\" content=\"here\"].</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.9 - 09/15/2016 - 09/16/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Theme now supports sub-sub menu.</li>\r\n<li>Block grid has a new options <code>gutter</code>, <code>gutter_lower</code>, and <code>animate</code> . See the docs for more information.</li>\r\n<li>Icon Schema has been deprecated.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode Schema.</li>\r\n<li>Theme now supports companies with Fax numbers.</li>\r\n<li>BXSlider has been deprecated to make the switch to Slick Carousel. <a href=\"https://kenwheeler.github.io/slick/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link-color-2\">Slick Docs</a></li>\r\n<li>New shortcodes for slider. See the docs for more info.</a></li>\r\n<li>Slider, match height, and waypoints are no longer optional plugins. The theme relies on these too often so they are by default included in the theme.</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.8 - 09/12/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New class has been added <code>.section-split</code>. Using this class relies on your columns following a certain layout. See the docs for more info!</li>\r\n<li>A brand new page template has been added to the theme. This makes building over conversion pages (content left, sidebar right) a lot faster and it is basically automated now. When you create a new page, change the template to Sub Page Template and the rest is done for you. [anchor href=\"/page-template-sub-page/\" content=\"Here\"] is what the page looks like. If at any point you want to make edits to the template, just edit the <code>template-sub-page.php</code> file.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.7 - 09/09/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Stellar.JS has been added to the theme. This is not an optional plugin, it needs to always stay in the theme. Stellar allows parallax backgrounds. There is a new option on the section shortcode and the page_banner_large shortcode. Simply just set parallax=\"true\" and boom, you\'ll have parallax. Docs have been updated with new options.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.6 - 08/30/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New shortcode img_overlay</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode team_block</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode g_map</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.5 - 08/25/2016 - 08/29/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The excerpt read character length is now set to 20 characters. To change this, you can go into setup.php.</li>\r\n<li>The excerpt read more has been changed from WP\'s default [...] to just simply ... </li>\r\n<li>New tracking options for button and anchor.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode img_flex.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode page_banner_flex. </li>\r\n<li>Formulated mobile navbar calculations. </li>\r\n<li>The issue with nesting a col shortcode inside another col shortcode has been address. In WordPress you cannot nest shortcodes that use the same name, so nesting our column shortcode needed a work-around. If you want to nest a col inside another col you need to use <code>col_nested</code> for the nested columns. It works and has the same options as the col shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>The contact page form now has color validation. Red inset shadow gets added if req field is skipped over and green inset shadow is added if it has a value.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>ul\'s and ol\'s now have default 25px padding left and 10px margin bottom. Use <code>class=\"list-unstyled\"</code> if you don\'t want any styles to your list.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.4 - 08/23/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>New contact page form layout. There are by default two different forms. One that has labels and one that does not and uses placeholders instead.</li>\r\n<li>You can now toggle the admin bar on and off. This is especially useful when in development. Just uncomment the show_admin_bar(false) function to hide the admin bar.</li>\r\n<li>New LESS Mixin <code>placeholder-color(@color);</code>. See documentation for details.</li>\r\n<li>New classes <code>link-blend</code> <code>text-right</code> <code>text-left</code>. See documentation for more details.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>Big fixes to navbar active page. All the active styles now apply correctly.</li>\r\n<li>Fix to last of type link in navbar. There was a bug were it was giving styles we didn\'t want to the sub menu.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.3 - 08/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>Footer, Mobile Nav, Topbar and more use address attributes from Global Content to populate contact data.</li>\r\n<li>Bug fix to the placehold shortcode where it would return one extra sentence then what you asked for.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.2 - 08/19/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>New grid layout on navbar & logo display block.</li>\r\n<li>No padding-right on last-of-type navbar link. (css in !important on this rule)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.1 - 08/18/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>If an anchor tag has <code>#</code> as the href attribute, it will no longer make the page jump or add \"#\" to the end of the URL. It will simply do nothing at all.</li>\r\n<li>Login page now has the BrandCoders logo and clicking that logo now takes you to brandcoders.com. If you want to change these settings, you can find them in <code>lib/setup.php</code>.</li>\r\n<li>A default \'Thank You\' page has been implemented into theme and is already linked up to default contact form.</li>\r\n<li>The default buttons paddings have been increased on all sizes. They have <a href=\"https://foundation.zurb.com/sites/docs/v/5.5.3/components/buttons.html#button-sizing\" target=\"_blank\">foundations</a> sizes. They are a pretty good standard.</li>\r\n<li>New max width classes have been implemented into the theme. See classes and mixins for the documentation.</li>\r\n<li>New class <code>iframe-container</code>. Give to an element that is the parent of an iframe. It will make the iframe responsive.</li>\r\n<li><code>.bg-color-1</code> and <code>.bg-color-2</code> are now standard classes. See classes and mixins for the documentation.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>Changes to comments in code and code organization.</li>\r\n<li>Navbar z-index changed to 2001</li>\r\n<li>Buttons don\'t have buggy styles on active and focus anymore.</li>\r\n<li>Contact Form 7 Submit Buttons now Automatically use <code>color-1</code>.</li>\r\n<li>A featured image for the overall theme has been added. This is the picture that is shown when your go to appearance->themes in the WordPress backend.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/section]','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','4-revision-v1','','','2017-07-13 14:15:01','2017-07-13 19:15:01','',4,'http://sushiexperience.com.test/4-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(2175,4,'2017-07-14 06:23:52','2017-07-14 11:23:52','[section container=\"true\" row=\"true\" full_col=\"true\"]\r\n<div class=\"text-center p15 mb20\" role=\"alert\" style=\"background: RGBA(252, 248, 227, 1.00)\">\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 20px;\">If you add a Shortcode(s) please <b>document it</b>. I created a <a href=\"http://sushiexperience.com.test/shortcodes/documentation-template/\"><b>template for documentation (click me)</b></a> that should make it easy to write some docs. This theme has had <b>multiple</b> updates since 3/10/2017 but the Patch Notes show the theme hasn\'t been updated in months. Anytime a change is made that impacts the theme or gives it added/changed functionality, it needs to be communicated in the Patch Notes and the themes Version needs to be changed (found in functions.php).</p>\r\n</div>\r\n[hr]\r\n<h1>Version [version]</h1>\r\n<h2>PATCH NOTES</h2>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.12.0 - 4/1/2017 - 7/13/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Changes to Accordion styles.</li>\r\n<li>Added new <a href=\"https://www.tippedjs.com/documentation\" target=\"_blank\">Tipped Tooltip</a> plugin. This hasn\'t been converted into a shortcode because of the way the markup needs to by laid out. See the <a href=\"/classes-and-mixins/tooltips/\">our docs</a> on how to use this tooltip.</li>\r\n<li>Updated Bower Components</li>\r\n<li>Brought in latest Font Awesome package.</li>\r\n<li>Created a basic <a href=\"http://sushiexperience.com.test/shortcodes/documentation-template/\">template for documentation</a>. Anytime a new shortcode is added, copy and paste the markup in that page as your starting point.</li>\r\n<li>New \"Example Local Service\" page template added</li>\r\n<li>New \"Example Professional Service\" page template added</li>\r\n<li>New \"Example Product Page\" template added</li>\r\n<li>Social Blocks shortcode added to display stylized social media blocks that tell users to \"Follow\".</li>\r\n<li>Social Sharing Squares shortcode added which share the content on a blog post through the user\'s social media account.</li>\r\n<li>Mobile Top CTA shortcode added along with capability to change buttons in the WYSIWIG editor.</li>\r\n<li>Middle CTA shortcode added that can be fully customized.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.11.1 -  3/10/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>back-up in project folder</li>\r\n<li>Brand New Mobile Menu</li>\r\n<li>The Desktop Menu and Mobile Menu no longer share the same links. You\'ll need to modify the mobile menu in the wordpress backend when you set up the primary menu.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.9 - 3/7/2017 - 3/8/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><code>single-event.php</code> has been rebuilt to better accommodate content and pictures.</li>\r\n<li>New example page \'Home\'</li>\r\n<li>The `gutter` and `gutter_bottom` options from Block Grid have now been added to the gallery shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>All Styles are being enqued the \"right\" way. The bottom of functions.php has this code if your interested on how this is done.</li>\r\n<li>All JavaScript is being enqued the \"right\" way. The bottom of functions.php has this code if your interested on how this is done.</li>\r\n<li>Added CSS prefixes throughout less files.</li>\r\n<li>Same height for event system loop.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.8 - 3/7/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Plugin updates.</li>\r\n<li>Font Weight Classes Added. <code>.fw-{desired-font-weight}</code></li>\r\n<li>The max-width classes bug is gone.</li>\r\n<li>Removed trash ass parallax plugin. </li>\r\n<li>New option <code>full_col</code> for the section shortcode. See the docs for the details.</li>\r\n<li>The <code>placehold</code> shortcode is now for LOREM IPSUM TEXT ONLY. The only new REQUIRED option is <code>lines=\"\"</code> where you feed the number of sentences.</li>\r\n<li>New option for the <code>bc_img</code> shortcode <code>dummy</code>. Since we use a lot of placeholder images, this option gives you the opportunity to feed ONLY THE DIMENSIONS to it and it will output a dummy image based on the dimensions given.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.7 - 3/3/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New file in <code>lib</code> for custom taxonomies. There is a basic function in that file that is commented out that will create a custom taxonomy, but a few of the $args need to change depending on the post type your trying to target with the custom tax.</li>\r\n<li>A lot of the CSS for the navbar has been cleaned up a lot. There was a specificity issue with the styles and sub menu was getting styles from top level links and all sorts of whack other stuff. This is all fixed now.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.6 - 2/24/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>There is a new textblock that will output a form for mailchimp. If you go into <code>mailchimpAjaxHandler.php</code> and pass your API Key and List ID to the proper variables, the form will do the rest for you. Again, this textblock WILL NOT work if you haven\'t set up those variables.</li>\r\n<li>A lot of the animation classes got an upgrade. Smoother, more linear look and they activate earlier instead of having to scroll all the way into the viewport to start the animation</li>\r\n<li>New function in functions.php called <code>build_event_schema($id)</code>. This function is only useable in a PhP file. You need to feed the <code>$post->ID</code> to the function and it will output proper Schema for the event in which you feed the id Event. Schema can be tested <a href=\"https://search.google.com/structured-data/testing-tool\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></li>\r\n<li>There is now a function for signing up subscribers to mailchimp that is easily used with an ajax call to the file.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.5 - 2/21/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[past_event_loop]]</code>. This will output the events that have passed. You need to have the Event module set up in order for this shortcode to execute.</li>\r\n<li>Clean up of some code</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.4 - 2/6/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li> New shortcode <code>[[bc_box]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li> New shortcode <code>[[image_slider]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li>General bug fixes and improvements.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.3 - 1/31/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Parallax is back! You can use this on the section, page banner and page banner large. just set parallax=\"true\" and make sure you give it a background=\"\".</li>\r\n<li>New mobile navbar layout</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.2 - 12/13/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reduced the padding on the contact form on mobile</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[bc_counter]]</code></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.1 - 12/12/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reduced the padding on the contact form on mobile</li>\r\n<li>New helpful script, Pressing <code>SHIFT + Z</code> (on the front end) will toggle the wpadminbar to show and not show.</li>\r\n<li>Board of Directors added.</li>\r\n<li>Style changes to the <a href=\"/blog/\">blog</a> loop</li>\r\n<li>Contact form error styles are better</li>\r\n<li>Set admin columns for Staff and Event posts</li>\r\n<li>single-staff.php added.</li>\r\n<li>LESS code cleanup</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[section_overlay_blend]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[share_links]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li>Changed some default fonts so these docs are nicer looking.</li>\r\n<li>New class - class=\"lh1\". Gives an element line-height: 1;</li>\r\n<li>More Demo Pages Added, see <a href=\"/modules/\">modules</a>.</li>\r\n<li>Few new animation classes created. <code>bc-fade-in-left</code> and <code>bc-fade-in-right</code>. Throw these on any element and it will fade in when scrolled to.</li>\r\n<li>New documentation page for Modules. This page explains how to use the newly implemented systems that take some configuration before starting to use them.</li>\r\n<li>New javascript file added called theme.js. This file was added to house all the javascript that is necessary for the theme to work properly. The main.js file was getting really crowded and it should now be used for website specific scripts.</li>\r\n<li>Bye Steph, your not a user anymore. Pwned.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode social_inline. See the docs for the details.</li>\r\n<li>New class text-fade added to the theme. Give to a piece of text, header, etc. and it will fade in when scrolled to.</li>\r\n<li>the img_overlay shortcode has been modified to look and work cleaner.</li>\r\n<li>The img shortcode has been modified. See the docs for all the new options.</li>\r\n<li>Change made to the header. We kept the Columns but just pulled the padding from them, so everything should work more fluidly.</li>\r\n<li>Admin Columns Pro with the ACF add-on has been added to the plugins.</li>\r\n<li>The staff system that was first implemented on UAP has been added to the theme. To get everything going, you need to uncomment the custom post type staff and use the <code>bc_staff_grid</code> shortcode. All the styles and javascript are ready to go. Styles can be found in textblocks-and-shortcodes.</li>\r\n<li>Food Menu system added to the theme. To get it going, make a page and set the template to Featured Menu and your good to go. Styles can be found in textblocks-shortcodes less file.</li>\r\n<li>Hours option added to Schema, Address Loop and Mobile Location Conversion shortcodes.</li>\r\n<li>Caption option added to the gallery shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>Custom Role code updated to have further control over custom roles.</li>\r\n<li>Event System added. To set up, active custom posts types in functions and the event post is already built into the custom post file. You also need to set the event custom fields to match post type event. Styles for the event card and single event are found in textblocks-shortcodes.less</li>\r\n<li>ALL bower components (such as bootstrap, slick, jquery, matchHeight, FontAwesome, etc) have all been updated to their most recent version available as of 11/16/2016.</li>\r\n<li>Libraries and Frameworks in Global Content has been deprecated, we\'re just going to bring in all the Bower Components.</li>\r\n<li>Business Hours added to the Global Content page, with the address and such.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed a bug with Gallery shortcode where the image wasn\'t responsive.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.17 - 11/8/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A 768x768 placeholder image has been added to the media uploads. We always seem to need placeholder post images and placeholder staff images, etc, so this will be nice to have in the media folder.</li>\r\n<li>There are no longer different footer layouts. The layout just lives in footer.php now</li>\r\n<li><code>mobile-text-center</code> class has been added to center on viewports under 768px.</li>\r\n<li>Change to the mobile nav dropdown links. There was an issue that if there were too many links, you weren\'t able to scroll down the mobile nav links, it would scroll the page behind it. That has now been fixed.</li>\r\n<li>search function now available for mobile. The variable to toggle it is in header.php</li>\r\n<li>the shortcode <code>single_location_address</code> has been deprecated. Just use <code>schema</code> instead.</li>\r\n<li>new option for the address_attr shortcode - <code>link</code>. See the <a href=\"/shortcodes/address-attribute/\">docs</a> for how to use it. </li>\r\n<li>container-fluid option now available for the section shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed a bug with Gallery shortcode where the image wasn\'t responsive.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.16 - 11/2/2016 - 11/3/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Breadcrumbs now have schema</li>\r\n<li>Search function now a part of the theme.</li>\r\n<li>Visual editor has been disabled for ALL USERS. (code for this is found in /lib/setup.php)</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The buttons for the mobile footer have been re-vamped to fit better.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.15 - 10/26/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Drop down menu for mobile is now a lot easier to touch on a mobile device, as well as having a new look.</a>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Changed some default accordion styles.</li>\r\n<li>Removed the formula we previously had for calculating height of logo for the navbar and spacing etc. It just wasn\'t consistent enough and all depended on what the companies logo looks like.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.14 - 10/21/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New classes added to change text color to the LESS variables color-1 and color-2</li>\r\n<li>Removed Stellar JS (the parallax plugin). It was way too buggy. We will need to investigate a new parallax option. This means that you can no longer use the \'parallax\' option for some of our shortcodes. Avoid using that option until further notice.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed bug with Block Grid that was causing it to always go 2 across on mobile.</li>\r\n<li>Removed some Text Blocks we never use.</li>\r\n<li>Section Split has been fixed to work better on all viewports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.13 - 09/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Minor fix to the video bg plugin.</li>\r\n<li>Big improvement to the <a href=\"/blog/\">blog</a> template.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The mobile logo and desktop logo for the navbar are now variables. Just plug in the path/to/file and it\'ll get injected for you.</li>\r\n<li>Changes visually to the sidebar with form textblock.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.12 - 09/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>So yea... section_video is gone. But fear not! We just made it easier to execute a video background. It is now built into the regular <code>section</code> shortcode. Peep the docs.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.11 - 09/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><code>underlay</code> option had been added to the <code>section</code> shortcode. Peep the docs for the 411.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.10 - 09/21/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><code>target</code> option added to bc_btn shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>New legitness section_video. Find out more about this badass shortcode [anchor href=\"http://sushiexperience.com.test/shortcodes/section-video/\" content=\"here\"].</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.9 - 09/15/2016 - 09/16/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Theme now supports sub-sub menu.</li>\r\n<li>Block grid has a new options <code>gutter</code>, <code>gutter_lower</code>, and <code>animate</code> . See the docs for more information.</li>\r\n<li>Icon Schema has been deprecated.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode Schema.</li>\r\n<li>Theme now supports companies with Fax numbers.</li>\r\n<li>BXSlider has been deprecated to make the switch to Slick Carousel. <a href=\"https://kenwheeler.github.io/slick/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link-color-2\">Slick Docs</a></li>\r\n<li>New shortcodes for slider. See the docs for more info.</a></li>\r\n<li>Slider, match height, and waypoints are no longer optional plugins. The theme relies on these too often so they are by default included in the theme.</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.8 - 09/12/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New class has been added <code>.section-split</code>. Using this class relies on your columns following a certain layout. See the docs for more info!</li>\r\n<li>A brand new page template has been added to the theme. This makes building over conversion pages (content left, sidebar right) a lot faster and it is basically automated now. When you create a new page, change the template to Sub Page Template and the rest is done for you. [anchor href=\"/page-template-sub-page/\" content=\"Here\"] is what the page looks like. If at any point you want to make edits to the template, just edit the <code>template-sub-page.php</code> file.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.7 - 09/09/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Stellar.JS has been added to the theme. This is not an optional plugin, it needs to always stay in the theme. Stellar allows parallax backgrounds. There is a new option on the section shortcode and the page_banner_large shortcode. Simply just set parallax=\"true\" and boom, you\'ll have parallax. Docs have been updated with new options.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.6 - 08/30/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New shortcode img_overlay</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode team_block</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode g_map</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.5 - 08/25/2016 - 08/29/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The excerpt read character length is now set to 20 characters. To change this, you can go into setup.php.</li>\r\n<li>The excerpt read more has been changed from WP\'s default [...] to just simply ... </li>\r\n<li>New tracking options for button and anchor.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode img_flex.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode page_banner_flex. </li>\r\n<li>Formulated mobile navbar calculations. </li>\r\n<li>The issue with nesting a col shortcode inside another col shortcode has been address. In WordPress you cannot nest shortcodes that use the same name, so nesting our column shortcode needed a work-around. If you want to nest a col inside another col you need to use <code>col_nested</code> for the nested columns. It works and has the same options as the col shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>The contact page form now has color validation. Red inset shadow gets added if req field is skipped over and green inset shadow is added if it has a value.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>ul\'s and ol\'s now have default 25px padding left and 10px margin bottom. Use <code>class=\"list-unstyled\"</code> if you don\'t want any styles to your list.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.4 - 08/23/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>New contact page form layout. There are by default two different forms. One that has labels and one that does not and uses placeholders instead.</li>\r\n<li>You can now toggle the admin bar on and off. This is especially useful when in development. Just uncomment the show_admin_bar(false) function to hide the admin bar.</li>\r\n<li>New LESS Mixin <code>placeholder-color(@color);</code>. See documentation for details.</li>\r\n<li>New classes <code>link-blend</code> <code>text-right</code> <code>text-left</code>. See documentation for more details.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>Big fixes to navbar active page. All the active styles now apply correctly.</li>\r\n<li>Fix to last of type link in navbar. There was a bug were it was giving styles we didn\'t want to the sub menu.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.3 - 08/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>Footer, Mobile Nav, Topbar and more use address attributes from Global Content to populate contact data.</li>\r\n<li>Bug fix to the placehold shortcode where it would return one extra sentence then what you asked for.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.2 - 08/19/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>New grid layout on navbar & logo display block.</li>\r\n<li>No padding-right on last-of-type navbar link. (css in !important on this rule)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.1 - 08/18/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>If an anchor tag has <code>#</code> as the href attribute, it will no longer make the page jump or add \"#\" to the end of the URL. It will simply do nothing at all.</li>\r\n<li>Login page now has the BrandCoders logo and clicking that logo now takes you to brandcoders.com. If you want to change these settings, you can find them in <code>lib/setup.php</code>.</li>\r\n<li>A default \'Thank You\' page has been implemented into theme and is already linked up to default contact form.</li>\r\n<li>The default buttons paddings have been increased on all sizes. They have <a href=\"https://foundation.zurb.com/sites/docs/v/5.5.3/components/buttons.html#button-sizing\" target=\"_blank\">foundations</a> sizes. They are a pretty good standard.</li>\r\n<li>New max width classes have been implemented into the theme. See classes and mixins for the documentation.</li>\r\n<li>New class <code>iframe-container</code>. Give to an element that is the parent of an iframe. It will make the iframe responsive.</li>\r\n<li><code>.bg-color-1</code> and <code>.bg-color-2</code> are now standard classes. See classes and mixins for the documentation.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>Changes to comments in code and code organization.</li>\r\n<li>Navbar z-index changed to 2001</li>\r\n<li>Buttons don\'t have buggy styles on active and focus anymore.</li>\r\n<li>Contact Form 7 Submit Buttons now Automatically use <code>color-1</code>.</li>\r\n<li>A featured image for the overall theme has been added. This is the picture that is shown when your go to appearance->themes in the WordPress backend.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/section]','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','4-revision-v1','','','2017-07-14 06:23:52','2017-07-14 11:23:52','',4,'http://sushiexperience.com.test/4-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(2176,4,'2017-07-14 06:44:07','2017-07-14 11:44:07','[section container=\"true\" row=\"true\" full_col=\"true\"]\r\n<div class=\"text-center p15 mb20\" role=\"alert\" style=\"background: RGBA(252, 248, 227, 1.00)\">\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 20px;\">If you add a Shortcode(s) please <b>document it</b>. I created a <a href=\"http://sushiexperience.com.test/shortcodes/documentation-template/\"><b>template for documentation (click me)</b></a> that should make it easy to write some docs. This theme has had <b>multiple</b> updates since 3/10/2017 but the Patch Notes show the theme hasn\'t been updated in months. Anytime a change is made that impacts the theme or gives it added/changed functionality, it needs to be communicated in the Patch Notes and the themes Version needs to be changed (found in functions.php).</p>\r\n</div>\r\n[doc_shortcode]\r\n[hr]\r\n[/doc_shortcode]\r\n<h1>Version [version]</h1>\r\n<h2>PATCH NOTES</h2>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.12.0 - 4/1/2017 - 7/13/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Changes to Accordion styles.</li>\r\n<li>Added new <a href=\"https://www.tippedjs.com/documentation\" target=\"_blank\">Tipped Tooltip</a> plugin. This hasn\'t been converted into a shortcode because of the way the markup needs to by laid out. See the <a href=\"/classes-and-mixins/tooltips/\">our docs</a> on how to use this tooltip.</li>\r\n<li>Updated Bower Components</li>\r\n<li>Brought in latest Font Awesome package.</li>\r\n<li>Created a basic <a href=\"http://sushiexperience.com.test/shortcodes/documentation-template/\">template for documentation</a>. Anytime a new shortcode is added, copy and paste the markup in that page as your starting point.</li>\r\n<li>New \"Example Local Service\" page template added</li>\r\n<li>New \"Example Professional Service\" page template added</li>\r\n<li>New \"Example Product Page\" template added</li>\r\n<li>Social Blocks shortcode added to display stylized social media blocks that tell users to \"Follow\".</li>\r\n<li>Social Sharing Squares shortcode added which share the content on a blog post through the user\'s social media account.</li>\r\n<li>Mobile Top CTA shortcode added along with capability to change buttons in the WYSIWIG editor.</li>\r\n<li>Middle CTA shortcode added that can be fully customized.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.11.1 -  3/10/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>back-up in project folder</li>\r\n<li>Brand New Mobile Menu</li>\r\n<li>The Desktop Menu and Mobile Menu no longer share the same links. You\'ll need to modify the mobile menu in the wordpress backend when you set up the primary menu.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.9 - 3/7/2017 - 3/8/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><code>single-event.php</code> has been rebuilt to better accommodate content and pictures.</li>\r\n<li>New example page \'Home\'</li>\r\n<li>The `gutter` and `gutter_bottom` options from Block Grid have now been added to the gallery shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>All Styles are being enqued the \"right\" way. The bottom of functions.php has this code if your interested on how this is done.</li>\r\n<li>All JavaScript is being enqued the \"right\" way. The bottom of functions.php has this code if your interested on how this is done.</li>\r\n<li>Added CSS prefixes throughout less files.</li>\r\n<li>Same height for event system loop.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.8 - 3/7/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Plugin updates.</li>\r\n<li>Font Weight Classes Added. <code>.fw-{desired-font-weight}</code></li>\r\n<li>The max-width classes bug is gone.</li>\r\n<li>Removed trash ass parallax plugin. </li>\r\n<li>New option <code>full_col</code> for the section shortcode. See the docs for the details.</li>\r\n<li>The <code>placehold</code> shortcode is now for LOREM IPSUM TEXT ONLY. The only new REQUIRED option is <code>lines=\"\"</code> where you feed the number of sentences.</li>\r\n<li>New option for the <code>bc_img</code> shortcode <code>dummy</code>. Since we use a lot of placeholder images, this option gives you the opportunity to feed ONLY THE DIMENSIONS to it and it will output a dummy image based on the dimensions given.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.7 - 3/3/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New file in <code>lib</code> for custom taxonomies. There is a basic function in that file that is commented out that will create a custom taxonomy, but a few of the $args need to change depending on the post type your trying to target with the custom tax.</li>\r\n<li>A lot of the CSS for the navbar has been cleaned up a lot. There was a specificity issue with the styles and sub menu was getting styles from top level links and all sorts of whack other stuff. This is all fixed now.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.6 - 2/24/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>There is a new textblock that will output a form for mailchimp. If you go into <code>mailchimpAjaxHandler.php</code> and pass your API Key and List ID to the proper variables, the form will do the rest for you. Again, this textblock WILL NOT work if you haven\'t set up those variables.</li>\r\n<li>A lot of the animation classes got an upgrade. Smoother, more linear look and they activate earlier instead of having to scroll all the way into the viewport to start the animation</li>\r\n<li>New function in functions.php called <code>build_event_schema($id)</code>. This function is only useable in a PhP file. You need to feed the <code>$post->ID</code> to the function and it will output proper Schema for the event in which you feed the id Event. Schema can be tested <a href=\"https://search.google.com/structured-data/testing-tool\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></li>\r\n<li>There is now a function for signing up subscribers to mailchimp that is easily used with an ajax call to the file.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.5 - 2/21/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[past_event_loop]]</code>. This will output the events that have passed. You need to have the Event module set up in order for this shortcode to execute.</li>\r\n<li>Clean up of some code</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.4 - 2/6/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li> New shortcode <code>[[bc_box]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li> New shortcode <code>[[image_slider]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li>General bug fixes and improvements.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.3 - 1/31/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Parallax is back! You can use this on the section, page banner and page banner large. just set parallax=\"true\" and make sure you give it a background=\"\".</li>\r\n<li>New mobile navbar layout</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.2 - 12/13/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reduced the padding on the contact form on mobile</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[bc_counter]]</code></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.1 - 12/12/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reduced the padding on the contact form on mobile</li>\r\n<li>New helpful script, Pressing <code>SHIFT + Z</code> (on the front end) will toggle the wpadminbar to show and not show.</li>\r\n<li>Board of Directors added.</li>\r\n<li>Style changes to the <a href=\"/blog/\">blog</a> loop</li>\r\n<li>Contact form error styles are better</li>\r\n<li>Set admin columns for Staff and Event posts</li>\r\n<li>single-staff.php added.</li>\r\n<li>LESS code cleanup</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[section_overlay_blend]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[share_links]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li>Changed some default fonts so these docs are nicer looking.</li>\r\n<li>New class - class=\"lh1\". Gives an element line-height: 1;</li>\r\n<li>More Demo Pages Added, see <a href=\"/modules/\">modules</a>.</li>\r\n<li>Few new animation classes created. <code>bc-fade-in-left</code> and <code>bc-fade-in-right</code>. Throw these on any element and it will fade in when scrolled to.</li>\r\n<li>New documentation page for Modules. This page explains how to use the newly implemented systems that take some configuration before starting to use them.</li>\r\n<li>New javascript file added called theme.js. This file was added to house all the javascript that is necessary for the theme to work properly. The main.js file was getting really crowded and it should now be used for website specific scripts.</li>\r\n<li>Bye Steph, your not a user anymore. Pwned.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode social_inline. See the docs for the details.</li>\r\n<li>New class text-fade added to the theme. Give to a piece of text, header, etc. and it will fade in when scrolled to.</li>\r\n<li>the img_overlay shortcode has been modified to look and work cleaner.</li>\r\n<li>The img shortcode has been modified. See the docs for all the new options.</li>\r\n<li>Change made to the header. We kept the Columns but just pulled the padding from them, so everything should work more fluidly.</li>\r\n<li>Admin Columns Pro with the ACF add-on has been added to the plugins.</li>\r\n<li>The staff system that was first implemented on UAP has been added to the theme. To get everything going, you need to uncomment the custom post type staff and use the <code>bc_staff_grid</code> shortcode. All the styles and javascript are ready to go. Styles can be found in textblocks-and-shortcodes.</li>\r\n<li>Food Menu system added to the theme. To get it going, make a page and set the template to Featured Menu and your good to go. Styles can be found in textblocks-shortcodes less file.</li>\r\n<li>Hours option added to Schema, Address Loop and Mobile Location Conversion shortcodes.</li>\r\n<li>Caption option added to the gallery shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>Custom Role code updated to have further control over custom roles.</li>\r\n<li>Event System added. To set up, active custom posts types in functions and the event post is already built into the custom post file. You also need to set the event custom fields to match post type event. Styles for the event card and single event are found in textblocks-shortcodes.less</li>\r\n<li>ALL bower components (such as bootstrap, slick, jquery, matchHeight, FontAwesome, etc) have all been updated to their most recent version available as of 11/16/2016.</li>\r\n<li>Libraries and Frameworks in Global Content has been deprecated, we\'re just going to bring in all the Bower Components.</li>\r\n<li>Business Hours added to the Global Content page, with the address and such.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed a bug with Gallery shortcode where the image wasn\'t responsive.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.17 - 11/8/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A 768x768 placeholder image has been added to the media uploads. We always seem to need placeholder post images and placeholder staff images, etc, so this will be nice to have in the media folder.</li>\r\n<li>There are no longer different footer layouts. The layout just lives in footer.php now</li>\r\n<li><code>mobile-text-center</code> class has been added to center on viewports under 768px.</li>\r\n<li>Change to the mobile nav dropdown links. There was an issue that if there were too many links, you weren\'t able to scroll down the mobile nav links, it would scroll the page behind it. That has now been fixed.</li>\r\n<li>search function now available for mobile. The variable to toggle it is in header.php</li>\r\n<li>the shortcode <code>single_location_address</code> has been deprecated. Just use <code>schema</code> instead.</li>\r\n<li>new option for the address_attr shortcode - <code>link</code>. See the <a href=\"/shortcodes/address-attribute/\">docs</a> for how to use it. </li>\r\n<li>container-fluid option now available for the section shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed a bug with Gallery shortcode where the image wasn\'t responsive.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.16 - 11/2/2016 - 11/3/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Breadcrumbs now have schema</li>\r\n<li>Search function now a part of the theme.</li>\r\n<li>Visual editor has been disabled for ALL USERS. (code for this is found in /lib/setup.php)</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The buttons for the mobile footer have been re-vamped to fit better.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.15 - 10/26/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Drop down menu for mobile is now a lot easier to touch on a mobile device, as well as having a new look.</a>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Changed some default accordion styles.</li>\r\n<li>Removed the formula we previously had for calculating height of logo for the navbar and spacing etc. It just wasn\'t consistent enough and all depended on what the companies logo looks like.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.14 - 10/21/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New classes added to change text color to the LESS variables color-1 and color-2</li>\r\n<li>Removed Stellar JS (the parallax plugin). It was way too buggy. We will need to investigate a new parallax option. This means that you can no longer use the \'parallax\' option for some of our shortcodes. Avoid using that option until further notice.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed bug with Block Grid that was causing it to always go 2 across on mobile.</li>\r\n<li>Removed some Text Blocks we never use.</li>\r\n<li>Section Split has been fixed to work better on all viewports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.13 - 09/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Minor fix to the video bg plugin.</li>\r\n<li>Big improvement to the <a href=\"/blog/\">blog</a> template.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The mobile logo and desktop logo for the navbar are now variables. Just plug in the path/to/file and it\'ll get injected for you.</li>\r\n<li>Changes visually to the sidebar with form textblock.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.12 - 09/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>So yea... section_video is gone. But fear not! We just made it easier to execute a video background. It is now built into the regular <code>section</code> shortcode. Peep the docs.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.11 - 09/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><code>underlay</code> option had been added to the <code>section</code> shortcode. Peep the docs for the 411.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.10 - 09/21/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><code>target</code> option added to bc_btn shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>New legitness section_video. Find out more about this badass shortcode [anchor href=\"http://sushiexperience.com.test/shortcodes/section-video/\" content=\"here\"].</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.9 - 09/15/2016 - 09/16/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Theme now supports sub-sub menu.</li>\r\n<li>Block grid has a new options <code>gutter</code>, <code>gutter_lower</code>, and <code>animate</code> . See the docs for more information.</li>\r\n<li>Icon Schema has been deprecated.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode Schema.</li>\r\n<li>Theme now supports companies with Fax numbers.</li>\r\n<li>BXSlider has been deprecated to make the switch to Slick Carousel. <a href=\"https://kenwheeler.github.io/slick/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link-color-2\">Slick Docs</a></li>\r\n<li>New shortcodes for slider. See the docs for more info.</a></li>\r\n<li>Slider, match height, and waypoints are no longer optional plugins. The theme relies on these too often so they are by default included in the theme.</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.8 - 09/12/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New class has been added <code>.section-split</code>. Using this class relies on your columns following a certain layout. See the docs for more info!</li>\r\n<li>A brand new page template has been added to the theme. This makes building over conversion pages (content left, sidebar right) a lot faster and it is basically automated now. When you create a new page, change the template to Sub Page Template and the rest is done for you. [anchor href=\"/page-template-sub-page/\" content=\"Here\"] is what the page looks like. If at any point you want to make edits to the template, just edit the <code>template-sub-page.php</code> file.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.7 - 09/09/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Stellar.JS has been added to the theme. This is not an optional plugin, it needs to always stay in the theme. Stellar allows parallax backgrounds. There is a new option on the section shortcode and the page_banner_large shortcode. Simply just set parallax=\"true\" and boom, you\'ll have parallax. Docs have been updated with new options.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.6 - 08/30/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New shortcode img_overlay</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode team_block</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode g_map</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.5 - 08/25/2016 - 08/29/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The excerpt read character length is now set to 20 characters. To change this, you can go into setup.php.</li>\r\n<li>The excerpt read more has been changed from WP\'s default [...] to just simply ... </li>\r\n<li>New tracking options for button and anchor.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode img_flex.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode page_banner_flex. </li>\r\n<li>Formulated mobile navbar calculations. </li>\r\n<li>The issue with nesting a col shortcode inside another col shortcode has been address. In WordPress you cannot nest shortcodes that use the same name, so nesting our column shortcode needed a work-around. If you want to nest a col inside another col you need to use <code>col_nested</code> for the nested columns. It works and has the same options as the col shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>The contact page form now has color validation. Red inset shadow gets added if req field is skipped over and green inset shadow is added if it has a value.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>ul\'s and ol\'s now have default 25px padding left and 10px margin bottom. Use <code>class=\"list-unstyled\"</code> if you don\'t want any styles to your list.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.4 - 08/23/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>New contact page form layout. There are by default two different forms. One that has labels and one that does not and uses placeholders instead.</li>\r\n<li>You can now toggle the admin bar on and off. This is especially useful when in development. Just uncomment the show_admin_bar(false) function to hide the admin bar.</li>\r\n<li>New LESS Mixin <code>placeholder-color(@color);</code>. See documentation for details.</li>\r\n<li>New classes <code>link-blend</code> <code>text-right</code> <code>text-left</code>. See documentation for more details.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>Big fixes to navbar active page. All the active styles now apply correctly.</li>\r\n<li>Fix to last of type link in navbar. There was a bug were it was giving styles we didn\'t want to the sub menu.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.3 - 08/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>Footer, Mobile Nav, Topbar and more use address attributes from Global Content to populate contact data.</li>\r\n<li>Bug fix to the placehold shortcode where it would return one extra sentence then what you asked for.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.2 - 08/19/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>New grid layout on navbar & logo display block.</li>\r\n<li>No padding-right on last-of-type navbar link. (css in !important on this rule)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.1 - 08/18/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>If an anchor tag has <code>#</code> as the href attribute, it will no longer make the page jump or add \"#\" to the end of the URL. It will simply do nothing at all.</li>\r\n<li>Login page now has the BrandCoders logo and clicking that logo now takes you to brandcoders.com. If you want to change these settings, you can find them in <code>lib/setup.php</code>.</li>\r\n<li>A default \'Thank You\' page has been implemented into theme and is already linked up to default contact form.</li>\r\n<li>The default buttons paddings have been increased on all sizes. They have <a href=\"https://foundation.zurb.com/sites/docs/v/5.5.3/components/buttons.html#button-sizing\" target=\"_blank\">foundations</a> sizes. They are a pretty good standard.</li>\r\n<li>New max width classes have been implemented into the theme. See classes and mixins for the documentation.</li>\r\n<li>New class <code>iframe-container</code>. Give to an element that is the parent of an iframe. It will make the iframe responsive.</li>\r\n<li><code>.bg-color-1</code> and <code>.bg-color-2</code> are now standard classes. See classes and mixins for the documentation.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>Changes to comments in code and code organization.</li>\r\n<li>Navbar z-index changed to 2001</li>\r\n<li>Buttons don\'t have buggy styles on active and focus anymore.</li>\r\n<li>Contact Form 7 Submit Buttons now Automatically use <code>color-1</code>.</li>\r\n<li>A featured image for the overall theme has been added. This is the picture that is shown when your go to appearance->themes in the WordPress backend.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/section]','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','4-revision-v1','','','2017-07-14 06:44:07','2017-07-14 11:44:07','',4,'http://sushiexperience.com.test/4-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(2177,4,'2017-07-14 06:45:32','2017-07-14 11:45:32','[section container=\"true\" row=\"true\" full_col=\"true\"]\r\n<div class=\"text-center p15 mb20\" role=\"alert\" style=\"background: RGBA(252, 248, 227, 1.00)\">\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 20px;\">If you add a Shortcode(s) please <b>document it</b>. I created a <a href=\"http://sushiexperience.com.test/shortcodes/documentation-template/\"><b>template for documentation (click me)</b></a> that should make it easy to write some docs. This theme has had <b>multiple</b> updates since 3/10/2017 but the Patch Notes show the theme hasn\'t been updated in months. Anytime a change is made that impacts the theme or gives it added/changed functionality, it needs to be communicated in the Patch Notes and the themes Version needs to be changed (found in functions.php).</p>\r\n</div>\r\n[doc_shortcode]\r\n[hr]\r\n[placehold lines=\"4\"]\r\n[/doc_shortcode]\r\n<h1>Version [version]</h1>\r\n<h2>PATCH NOTES</h2>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.12.0 - 4/1/2017 - 7/13/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Changes to Accordion styles.</li>\r\n<li>Added new <a href=\"https://www.tippedjs.com/documentation\" target=\"_blank\">Tipped Tooltip</a> plugin. This hasn\'t been converted into a shortcode because of the way the markup needs to by laid out. See the <a href=\"/classes-and-mixins/tooltips/\">our docs</a> on how to use this tooltip.</li>\r\n<li>Updated Bower Components</li>\r\n<li>Brought in latest Font Awesome package.</li>\r\n<li>Created a basic <a href=\"http://sushiexperience.com.test/shortcodes/documentation-template/\">template for documentation</a>. Anytime a new shortcode is added, copy and paste the markup in that page as your starting point.</li>\r\n<li>New \"Example Local Service\" page template added</li>\r\n<li>New \"Example Professional Service\" page template added</li>\r\n<li>New \"Example Product Page\" template added</li>\r\n<li>Social Blocks shortcode added to display stylized social media blocks that tell users to \"Follow\".</li>\r\n<li>Social Sharing Squares shortcode added which share the content on a blog post through the user\'s social media account.</li>\r\n<li>Mobile Top CTA shortcode added along with capability to change buttons in the WYSIWIG editor.</li>\r\n<li>Middle CTA shortcode added that can be fully customized.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.11.1 -  3/10/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>back-up in project folder</li>\r\n<li>Brand New Mobile Menu</li>\r\n<li>The Desktop Menu and Mobile Menu no longer share the same links. You\'ll need to modify the mobile menu in the wordpress backend when you set up the primary menu.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.9 - 3/7/2017 - 3/8/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><code>single-event.php</code> has been rebuilt to better accommodate content and pictures.</li>\r\n<li>New example page \'Home\'</li>\r\n<li>The `gutter` and `gutter_bottom` options from Block Grid have now been added to the gallery shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>All Styles are being enqued the \"right\" way. The bottom of functions.php has this code if your interested on how this is done.</li>\r\n<li>All JavaScript is being enqued the \"right\" way. The bottom of functions.php has this code if your interested on how this is done.</li>\r\n<li>Added CSS prefixes throughout less files.</li>\r\n<li>Same height for event system loop.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.8 - 3/7/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Plugin updates.</li>\r\n<li>Font Weight Classes Added. <code>.fw-{desired-font-weight}</code></li>\r\n<li>The max-width classes bug is gone.</li>\r\n<li>Removed trash ass parallax plugin. </li>\r\n<li>New option <code>full_col</code> for the section shortcode. See the docs for the details.</li>\r\n<li>The <code>placehold</code> shortcode is now for LOREM IPSUM TEXT ONLY. The only new REQUIRED option is <code>lines=\"\"</code> where you feed the number of sentences.</li>\r\n<li>New option for the <code>bc_img</code> shortcode <code>dummy</code>. Since we use a lot of placeholder images, this option gives you the opportunity to feed ONLY THE DIMENSIONS to it and it will output a dummy image based on the dimensions given.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.7 - 3/3/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New file in <code>lib</code> for custom taxonomies. There is a basic function in that file that is commented out that will create a custom taxonomy, but a few of the $args need to change depending on the post type your trying to target with the custom tax.</li>\r\n<li>A lot of the CSS for the navbar has been cleaned up a lot. There was a specificity issue with the styles and sub menu was getting styles from top level links and all sorts of whack other stuff. This is all fixed now.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.6 - 2/24/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>There is a new textblock that will output a form for mailchimp. If you go into <code>mailchimpAjaxHandler.php</code> and pass your API Key and List ID to the proper variables, the form will do the rest for you. Again, this textblock WILL NOT work if you haven\'t set up those variables.</li>\r\n<li>A lot of the animation classes got an upgrade. Smoother, more linear look and they activate earlier instead of having to scroll all the way into the viewport to start the animation</li>\r\n<li>New function in functions.php called <code>build_event_schema($id)</code>. This function is only useable in a PhP file. You need to feed the <code>$post->ID</code> to the function and it will output proper Schema for the event in which you feed the id Event. Schema can be tested <a href=\"https://search.google.com/structured-data/testing-tool\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></li>\r\n<li>There is now a function for signing up subscribers to mailchimp that is easily used with an ajax call to the file.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.5 - 2/21/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[past_event_loop]]</code>. This will output the events that have passed. You need to have the Event module set up in order for this shortcode to execute.</li>\r\n<li>Clean up of some code</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.4 - 2/6/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li> New shortcode <code>[[bc_box]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li> New shortcode <code>[[image_slider]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li>General bug fixes and improvements.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.3 - 1/31/2017</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Parallax is back! You can use this on the section, page banner and page banner large. just set parallax=\"true\" and make sure you give it a background=\"\".</li>\r\n<li>New mobile navbar layout</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.2 - 12/13/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reduced the padding on the contact form on mobile</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[bc_counter]]</code></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.10.1 - 12/12/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reduced the padding on the contact form on mobile</li>\r\n<li>New helpful script, Pressing <code>SHIFT + Z</code> (on the front end) will toggle the wpadminbar to show and not show.</li>\r\n<li>Board of Directors added.</li>\r\n<li>Style changes to the <a href=\"/blog/\">blog</a> loop</li>\r\n<li>Contact form error styles are better</li>\r\n<li>Set admin columns for Staff and Event posts</li>\r\n<li>single-staff.php added.</li>\r\n<li>LESS code cleanup</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[section_overlay_blend]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode <code>[[share_links]]</code>.</li>\r\n<li>Changed some default fonts so these docs are nicer looking.</li>\r\n<li>New class - class=\"lh1\". Gives an element line-height: 1;</li>\r\n<li>More Demo Pages Added, see <a href=\"/modules/\">modules</a>.</li>\r\n<li>Few new animation classes created. <code>bc-fade-in-left</code> and <code>bc-fade-in-right</code>. Throw these on any element and it will fade in when scrolled to.</li>\r\n<li>New documentation page for Modules. This page explains how to use the newly implemented systems that take some configuration before starting to use them.</li>\r\n<li>New javascript file added called theme.js. This file was added to house all the javascript that is necessary for the theme to work properly. The main.js file was getting really crowded and it should now be used for website specific scripts.</li>\r\n<li>Bye Steph, your not a user anymore. Pwned.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode social_inline. See the docs for the details.</li>\r\n<li>New class text-fade added to the theme. Give to a piece of text, header, etc. and it will fade in when scrolled to.</li>\r\n<li>the img_overlay shortcode has been modified to look and work cleaner.</li>\r\n<li>The img shortcode has been modified. See the docs for all the new options.</li>\r\n<li>Change made to the header. We kept the Columns but just pulled the padding from them, so everything should work more fluidly.</li>\r\n<li>Admin Columns Pro with the ACF add-on has been added to the plugins.</li>\r\n<li>The staff system that was first implemented on UAP has been added to the theme. To get everything going, you need to uncomment the custom post type staff and use the <code>bc_staff_grid</code> shortcode. All the styles and javascript are ready to go. Styles can be found in textblocks-and-shortcodes.</li>\r\n<li>Food Menu system added to the theme. To get it going, make a page and set the template to Featured Menu and your good to go. Styles can be found in textblocks-shortcodes less file.</li>\r\n<li>Hours option added to Schema, Address Loop and Mobile Location Conversion shortcodes.</li>\r\n<li>Caption option added to the gallery shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>Custom Role code updated to have further control over custom roles.</li>\r\n<li>Event System added. To set up, active custom posts types in functions and the event post is already built into the custom post file. You also need to set the event custom fields to match post type event. Styles for the event card and single event are found in textblocks-shortcodes.less</li>\r\n<li>ALL bower components (such as bootstrap, slick, jquery, matchHeight, FontAwesome, etc) have all been updated to their most recent version available as of 11/16/2016.</li>\r\n<li>Libraries and Frameworks in Global Content has been deprecated, we\'re just going to bring in all the Bower Components.</li>\r\n<li>Business Hours added to the Global Content page, with the address and such.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed a bug with Gallery shortcode where the image wasn\'t responsive.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.17 - 11/8/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A 768x768 placeholder image has been added to the media uploads. We always seem to need placeholder post images and placeholder staff images, etc, so this will be nice to have in the media folder.</li>\r\n<li>There are no longer different footer layouts. The layout just lives in footer.php now</li>\r\n<li><code>mobile-text-center</code> class has been added to center on viewports under 768px.</li>\r\n<li>Change to the mobile nav dropdown links. There was an issue that if there were too many links, you weren\'t able to scroll down the mobile nav links, it would scroll the page behind it. That has now been fixed.</li>\r\n<li>search function now available for mobile. The variable to toggle it is in header.php</li>\r\n<li>the shortcode <code>single_location_address</code> has been deprecated. Just use <code>schema</code> instead.</li>\r\n<li>new option for the address_attr shortcode - <code>link</code>. See the <a href=\"/shortcodes/address-attribute/\">docs</a> for how to use it. </li>\r\n<li>container-fluid option now available for the section shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed a bug with Gallery shortcode where the image wasn\'t responsive.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.16 - 11/2/2016 - 11/3/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Breadcrumbs now have schema</li>\r\n<li>Search function now a part of the theme.</li>\r\n<li>Visual editor has been disabled for ALL USERS. (code for this is found in /lib/setup.php)</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The buttons for the mobile footer have been re-vamped to fit better.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.15 - 10/26/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Drop down menu for mobile is now a lot easier to touch on a mobile device, as well as having a new look.</a>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Changed some default accordion styles.</li>\r\n<li>Removed the formula we previously had for calculating height of logo for the navbar and spacing etc. It just wasn\'t consistent enough and all depended on what the companies logo looks like.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.14 - 10/21/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New classes added to change text color to the LESS variables color-1 and color-2</li>\r\n<li>Removed Stellar JS (the parallax plugin). It was way too buggy. We will need to investigate a new parallax option. This means that you can no longer use the \'parallax\' option for some of our shortcodes. Avoid using that option until further notice.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed bug with Block Grid that was causing it to always go 2 across on mobile.</li>\r\n<li>Removed some Text Blocks we never use.</li>\r\n<li>Section Split has been fixed to work better on all viewports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn\">1.9.13 - 09/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Minor fix to the video bg plugin.</li>\r\n<li>Big improvement to the <a href=\"/blog/\">blog</a> template.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The mobile logo and desktop logo for the navbar are now variables. Just plug in the path/to/file and it\'ll get injected for you.</li>\r\n<li>Changes visually to the sidebar with form textblock.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.12 - 09/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>So yea... section_video is gone. But fear not! We just made it easier to execute a video background. It is now built into the regular <code>section</code> shortcode. Peep the docs.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.11 - 09/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><code>underlay</code> option had been added to the <code>section</code> shortcode. Peep the docs for the 411.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.10 - 09/21/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><code>target</code> option added to bc_btn shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>New legitness section_video. Find out more about this badass shortcode [anchor href=\"http://sushiexperience.com.test/shortcodes/section-video/\" content=\"here\"].</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.9 - 09/15/2016 - 09/16/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Theme now supports sub-sub menu.</li>\r\n<li>Block grid has a new options <code>gutter</code>, <code>gutter_lower</code>, and <code>animate</code> . See the docs for more information.</li>\r\n<li>Icon Schema has been deprecated.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode Schema.</li>\r\n<li>Theme now supports companies with Fax numbers.</li>\r\n<li>BXSlider has been deprecated to make the switch to Slick Carousel. <a href=\"https://kenwheeler.github.io/slick/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link-color-2\">Slick Docs</a></li>\r\n<li>New shortcodes for slider. See the docs for more info.</a></li>\r\n<li>Slider, match height, and waypoints are no longer optional plugins. The theme relies on these too often so they are by default included in the theme.</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.8 - 09/12/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New class has been added <code>.section-split</code>. Using this class relies on your columns following a certain layout. See the docs for more info!</li>\r\n<li>A brand new page template has been added to the theme. This makes building over conversion pages (content left, sidebar right) a lot faster and it is basically automated now. When you create a new page, change the template to Sub Page Template and the rest is done for you. [anchor href=\"/page-template-sub-page/\" content=\"Here\"] is what the page looks like. If at any point you want to make edits to the template, just edit the <code>template-sub-page.php</code> file.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.7 - 09/09/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Stellar.JS has been added to the theme. This is not an optional plugin, it needs to always stay in the theme. Stellar allows parallax backgrounds. There is a new option on the section shortcode and the page_banner_large shortcode. Simply just set parallax=\"true\" and boom, you\'ll have parallax. Docs have been updated with new options.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.6 - 08/30/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New shortcode img_overlay</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode team_block</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode g_map</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.5 - 08/25/2016 - 08/29/2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The excerpt read character length is now set to 20 characters. To change this, you can go into setup.php.</li>\r\n<li>The excerpt read more has been changed from WP\'s default [...] to just simply ... </li>\r\n<li>New tracking options for button and anchor.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode img_flex.</li>\r\n<li>New shortcode page_banner_flex. </li>\r\n<li>Formulated mobile navbar calculations. </li>\r\n<li>The issue with nesting a col shortcode inside another col shortcode has been address. In WordPress you cannot nest shortcodes that use the same name, so nesting our column shortcode needed a work-around. If you want to nest a col inside another col you need to use <code>col_nested</code> for the nested columns. It works and has the same options as the col shortcode.</li>\r\n<li>The contact page form now has color validation. Red inset shadow gets added if req field is skipped over and green inset shadow is added if it has a value.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>ul\'s and ol\'s now have default 25px padding left and 10px margin bottom. Use <code>class=\"list-unstyled\"</code> if you don\'t want any styles to your list.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.4 - 08/23/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>New contact page form layout. There are by default two different forms. One that has labels and one that does not and uses placeholders instead.</li>\r\n<li>You can now toggle the admin bar on and off. This is especially useful when in development. Just uncomment the show_admin_bar(false) function to hide the admin bar.</li>\r\n<li>New LESS Mixin <code>placeholder-color(@color);</code>. See documentation for details.</li>\r\n<li>New classes <code>link-blend</code> <code>text-right</code> <code>text-left</code>. See documentation for more details.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>Big fixes to navbar active page. All the active styles now apply correctly.</li>\r\n<li>Fix to last of type link in navbar. There was a bug were it was giving styles we didn\'t want to the sub menu.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.3 - 08/22/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>Footer, Mobile Nav, Topbar and more use address attributes from Global Content to populate contact data.</li>\r\n<li>Bug fix to the placehold shortcode where it would return one extra sentence then what you asked for.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.2 - 08/19/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>New grid layout on navbar & logo display block.</li>\r\n<li>No padding-right on last-of-type navbar link. (css in !important on this rule)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"mbn mt2xl\">1.9.1 - 08/18/2016</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>If an anchor tag has <code>#</code> as the href attribute, it will no longer make the page jump or add \"#\" to the end of the URL. It will simply do nothing at all.</li>\r\n<li>Login page now has the BrandCoders logo and clicking that logo now takes you to brandcoders.com. If you want to change these settings, you can find them in <code>lib/setup.php</code>.</li>\r\n<li>A default \'Thank You\' page has been implemented into theme and is already linked up to default contact form.</li>\r\n<li>The default buttons paddings have been increased on all sizes. They have <a href=\"https://foundation.zurb.com/sites/docs/v/5.5.3/components/buttons.html#button-sizing\" target=\"_blank\">foundations</a> sizes. They are a pretty good standard.</li>\r\n<li>New max width classes have been implemented into the theme. See classes and mixins for the documentation.</li>\r\n<li>New class <code>iframe-container</code>. Give to an element that is the parent of an iframe. It will make the iframe responsive.</li>\r\n<li><code>.bg-color-1</code> and <code>.bg-color-2</code> are now standard classes. See classes and mixins for the documentation.</li>\r\n<li>\r\nGeneral bug fixes and improvements: \r\n<ul class=\"\">\r\n<li>Changes to comments in code and code organization.</li>\r\n<li>Navbar z-index changed to 2001</li>\r\n<li>Buttons don\'t have buggy styles on active and focus anymore.</li>\r\n<li>Contact Form 7 Submit Buttons now Automatically use <code>color-1</code>.</li>\r\n<li>A featured image for the overall theme has been added. This is the picture that is shown when your go to appearance->themes in the WordPress backend.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/section]','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','4-revision-v1','','','2017-07-14 06:45:32','2017-07-14 11:45:32','',4,'http://sushiexperience.com.test/4-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
